WEBVTT

1
00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:46.320
<i>Yet another quick knockout for
Mason Dixon, almost perfunctory.</i>

2
00:01:46.480 --> 00:01:48.440
<i>The fans let him know
how they feel about it.</i>

3
00:01:48.600 --> 00:01:51.480
<i>Hide the women and children.
This could get ugly.</i>

4
00:01:51.640 --> 00:01:55.600
<i>This crowd does nothing to hide
its anger over this latest debacle.</i>

5
00:01:56.000 --> 00:01:58.720
<i>The fans are mad as hell.
They don't want to take it anymore.</i>

6
00:01:58.920 --> 00:02:01.680
<i>They seem to be blaming Dixon,
a good fighter, for the decline...</i>

7
00:02:01.840 --> 00:02:05.960
<i>... not only of the heavyweight-division
guys, but of the entire sport.</i>

8
00:02:06.120 --> 00:02:07.480
<i>They're actually pelting...</i>

9
00:02:07.640 --> 00:02:11.080
<i>... the undefeated heavyweight
champion of the world with ice.</i>

10
00:02:11.240 --> 00:02:14.760
<i>Maybe this angry, visceral reaction
will pressure Dixon to fight someone...</i>

11
00:02:14.960 --> 00:02:17.760
<i>... who can fight back for a change.
If there's somebody out there.</i>

12
00:02:17.920 --> 00:02:22.920
<i>All of boxing is hoping for a warrior
who thrills us with his passion.</i>

13
00:04:44.960 --> 00:04:46.960
Time goes by too fast.

14
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:50.280
Yeah? Not fast enough.

15
00:04:50.440 --> 00:04:52.560
- Your kid should've been here.
- That's all right.

16
00:04:52.720 --> 00:04:56.000
- No, it ain't all right.
- The kid gets a little busy sometimes.

17
00:04:56.200 --> 00:04:57.800
He don't get that busy.

18
00:04:58.080 --> 00:05:02.040
Let's not talk about it here, okay?
You're coming tonight, right?

19
00:05:02.240 --> 00:05:05.800
I'm working. I took the tour
the last three years.

20
00:05:05.960 --> 00:05:07.960
I know, but it's the anniversary.

21
00:05:08.120 --> 00:05:09.680
Fine. You got my word.

22
00:05:09.840 --> 00:05:14.120
I appreciate it, thank you.
I owe you, Paulie.

23
00:05:44.400 --> 00:05:47.440
Yo, Robert. What's going on?
Where have you been? You're late.

24
00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:51.720
No. I don't wanna hear this.
Look, your job performance...

25
00:05:51.920 --> 00:05:54.760
...is nowhere near good enough
to be pulling this.

26
00:05:54.920 --> 00:05:57.800
I don't give a damn who your father is.
You understand me?

27
00:05:57.960 --> 00:06:00.120
- All right. Now get out of here.
- Okay.

28
00:06:00.280 --> 00:06:01.960
Thank you, sir.

29
00:06:04.240 --> 00:06:06.440
Yo, Robert. Yo.

30
00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:08.280
- Hey, Rocky.
- Hey.

31
00:06:08.600 --> 00:06:09.760
- Hey, how you doing?
- Hey.

32
00:06:09.920 --> 00:06:11.360
What's up, champ?

33
00:06:11.520 --> 00:06:13.160
- You caught me off guard.
- I know.

34
00:06:13.320 --> 00:06:15.160
I wanted to catch you
before you got busy.

35
00:06:15.320 --> 00:06:16.920
Yeah, it gets busy up there.

36
00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:19.560
- So how you doing? Yeah?
- Real good. Yeah.

37
00:06:19.960 --> 00:06:22.840
- Yo, Rock!
- Yeah, how you doing?

38
00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:24.560
Yeah, real good.

39
00:06:24.720 --> 00:06:27.240
Listen, you wanna go out
and get some coffee?

40
00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:29.000
I'm kind of behind. Maybe later?

41
00:06:29.520 --> 00:06:32.440
Yeah. That'd be great. You ought to
come by the restaurant tonight.

42
00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:34.960
I can have something
made special for you.

43
00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:38.840
Tonight I can't. I got plans.
A few of the guys get together.

44
00:06:39.400 --> 00:06:41.960
- Did I do something wrong?
- What do you mean?

45
00:06:42.120 --> 00:06:44.680
Well, I don't know exactly
what I mean...

46
00:06:44.880 --> 00:06:48.640
...but I just think, like, when I come
here, you don't feel so comfortable.

47
00:06:48.840 --> 00:06:51.000
And I certainly don't wanna do that.

48
00:06:52.320 --> 00:06:55.240
- Well, you throw a big shadow.
- A big shadow?

49
00:06:55.400 --> 00:06:57.920
You're not gonna get anything done
down here, Robert.

50
00:06:58.080 --> 00:07:01.320
Well, if you're not gonna introduce me,
I will. Hi, I'm William Tomilson.

51
00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:03.560
- How you doing?
- Your son works for me.

52
00:07:04.080 --> 00:07:05.720
- It's a good job.
- Yeah.

53
00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:08.600
I've told Robert about 20 times
that I wanted to meet you.

54
00:07:08.760 --> 00:07:10.840
You're pretty busy,
which isn't a bad thing.

55
00:07:11.040 --> 00:07:13.320
- I get a little tied up.
- Grab a shot, will you?

56
00:07:13.880 --> 00:07:17.000
I may not get this chance again.
Old warhorses have to stick together.

57
00:07:17.160 --> 00:07:19.400
- The old horses, yeah.
- I'll tell you.

58
00:07:20.240 --> 00:07:23.160
- Good thing it's not your left.
- This makes you popular with people.

59
00:07:23.560 --> 00:07:26.360
- One, two, three.
- Finally, we get to meet.

60
00:07:26.520 --> 00:07:29.160
I gotta get going. It was nice
to meet you face to face.

61
00:07:29.320 --> 00:07:32.560
You take care of yourself.
Robert, I'll see you later.

62
00:07:34.840 --> 00:07:38.280
I gotta get going.
I'll change my plans for tonight.

63
00:07:38.440 --> 00:07:40.200
That'd be great.
I'm looking forward to it.

64
00:07:40.400 --> 00:07:41.760
- How you doing?
- Okay.

65
00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:43.640
- Okay.
- All right.

66
00:07:43.800 --> 00:07:47.080
And do not let those numbers
drive you crazy.

67
00:07:47.240 --> 00:07:51.120
- Too late.
- Use an eraser, get rid of all of them.

68
00:07:53.160 --> 00:07:54.320
- Yo, Rock.
- Hey, guys.

69
00:07:54.680 --> 00:07:56.680
- Hey, Rock.
- Hey, how you doing?

70
00:08:11.480 --> 00:08:12.440
There you go.

71
00:08:17.880 --> 00:08:21.200
It'll be about 10 tenths.
You guys take care, okay? You got it.

72
00:08:24.400 --> 00:08:26.320
I'll try a few of these later on.

73
00:08:27.120 --> 00:08:29.560
- It's good for baking.
- How much...?

74
00:08:29.720 --> 00:08:31.600
- Yo, Paul, what's the cost?
- 58.40, sir.

75
00:08:31.760 --> 00:08:34.080
All right, take it out of that.
I trust you.

76
00:08:36.280 --> 00:08:37.920
- How you doing?
- You're too generous.

77
00:08:38.080 --> 00:08:39.720
Not a problem.

78
00:08:55.200 --> 00:08:57.520
How you guys doing?

79
00:09:03.600 --> 00:09:05.640
How we doing, Isabel?

80
00:09:05.800 --> 00:09:08.080
Okay, except for the freebie
reading the Bible.

81
00:09:08.240 --> 00:09:10.600
- He's okay.
- Just because you fought him...

82
00:09:10.760 --> 00:09:13.520
...don't mean you gotta feed him.
He doesn't look like a fighter.

83
00:09:13.680 --> 00:09:15.280
Spider Rico could hit.

84
00:09:15.440 --> 00:09:17.920
- Listen, how's your stomach?
- It's okay.

85
00:09:18.120 --> 00:09:20.320
If you keep rubbing olive oil
on your stomach...

86
00:09:20.480 --> 00:09:22.400
...your kid's gonna be
born very strong.

87
00:09:22.560 --> 00:09:25.320
- Okay, Rocky. Whatever you say.
- No, really.

88
00:09:28.080 --> 00:09:30.560
- Yo, how you doing, Spider?
- God bless you, Rocky.

89
00:09:30.760 --> 00:09:31.920
Thanks.

90
00:09:37.040 --> 00:09:38.920
How you guys doing?

91
00:09:40.720 --> 00:09:44.360
Jose, can you make something special
for my kid who's coming tonight?

92
00:09:44.560 --> 00:09:45.800
No problemo.

93
00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:48.920
Good. I appreciate it.

94
00:09:50.600 --> 00:09:53.400
<i>Back and forth, back and forth,
give and take.</i>

95
00:09:53.560 --> 00:09:56.680
And then I went in there like an animal
and threw him into the corner...

96
00:09:56.880 --> 00:10:00.400
...and I unloaded everything I had.
Hook, hook, hook, left, left, left.

97
00:10:00.560 --> 00:10:03.080
But Creed, he kept
busting me back pretty good...

98
00:10:03.280 --> 00:10:05.120
...and the agony began to pile up.

99
00:10:05.280 --> 00:10:08.440
Then I heard the best sound
that I ever heard in my life...

100
00:10:08.600 --> 00:10:10.160
- The bell.
- That's right, the bell.

101
00:10:10.320 --> 00:10:13.360
I ain't never been so tired,
and I'm sitting in my corner.

102
00:10:13.520 --> 00:10:16.040
I'm trying to figure out
how to survive the last round...

103
00:10:16.240 --> 00:10:17.960
...when Mickey leans
into my ear and says:

104
00:10:18.160 --> 00:10:21.120
"Come on, get out there
and fight this guy hard, you bum.

105
00:10:21.280 --> 00:10:25.920
You gotta be first. You gotta be first."
I said, "Yo, Mick, if I could...

106
00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:28.720
- "I would."
...I would."

107
00:10:28.880 --> 00:10:30.120
The end.

108
00:10:55.760 --> 00:10:58.840
<i>Yet another quick knockout for
Mason Dixon, almost perfunctory.</i>

109
00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:01.560
<i>The fans let him know
how they feel about it.</i>

110
00:11:01.720 --> 00:11:03.240
<i>They're actually pelting...</i>

111
00:11:03.440 --> 00:11:07.840
<i>... the undefeated heavyweight
champion of the world with ice.</i>

112
00:11:12.680 --> 00:11:15.840
Hello, Adrian's. Yeah?

113
00:11:16.360 --> 00:11:20.520
Tell him you can't make it?
Yeah, I'll give him the message.

114
00:11:21.840 --> 00:11:25.800
I just kept hearing Mickey's voice
in my head over and over again.

115
00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:27.840
I just dug down,
and before you know it...

116
00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:31.080
...it was toe to toe and it was...
Excuse me.

117
00:11:31.240 --> 00:11:35.280
Your son said he can't make it.
He said he'll take a rain check. Okay?

118
00:11:48.160 --> 00:11:49.320
<i>Look at these birds.</i>

119
00:11:49.480 --> 00:11:52.160
<i>Don't these birds look like candy?
Flying candy?</i>

120
00:11:52.320 --> 00:11:54.160
<i>Hey, birdie,
you wanna fly me home?</i>

121
00:11:54.320 --> 00:11:56.720
You need somebody
to walk you home?

122
00:11:57.640 --> 00:11:58.560
<i>No?</i>

123
00:11:58.760 --> 00:12:03.440
It's a cold night. We need a few laughs
in our life. What do you think? Maybe?

124
00:12:04.080 --> 00:12:06.000
<i>Maybe? Maybe?</i>

125
00:12:06.160 --> 00:12:08.560
<i>Okay. Let's get out of here, okay?</i>

126
00:12:22.960 --> 00:12:25.280
That place ain't changed much
from last year.

127
00:12:25.440 --> 00:12:27.120
Are we done?

128
00:12:27.440 --> 00:12:29.520
Hey, how you doing, Mick?

129
00:12:32.280 --> 00:12:34.160
That sign is falling apart, Paulie.

130
00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:37.520
The whole world is falling apart.
Look at us.

131
00:12:37.680 --> 00:12:39.960
Don't talk crazy, Paulie.

132
00:12:40.200 --> 00:12:45.240
You know, I think if you live someplace
long enough, you are that place.

133
00:12:45.840 --> 00:12:48.280
I ain't no talking building.

134
00:12:48.440 --> 00:12:50.600
Come on, it's getting late, Rocko.

135
00:12:50.920 --> 00:12:53.520
I get a headache from this train.

136
00:13:12.640 --> 00:13:15.400
I remember when
she was standing there...

137
00:13:15.560 --> 00:13:19.080
...all nervous and shy,
with this little smile.

138
00:13:19.720 --> 00:13:22.760
And all I wanted her to do
was trust me.

139
00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:27.880
She did.

140
00:13:28.880 --> 00:13:31.240
- She did.
- You done?

141
00:13:46.160 --> 00:13:48.840
- How long are we staying here?
- Not long.

142
00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:51.240
Well, I'm glad they tore
this ice rink down.

143
00:13:51.440 --> 00:13:52.600
Come on.

144
00:13:52.760 --> 00:13:56.400
You heard me.
I'm happy they tore it apart.

145
00:13:59.920 --> 00:14:04.160
First time I walked your sister
across this ice, we was over there.

146
00:14:04.360 --> 00:14:07.680
She was nervous, but I wasn't so great
on the blades either.

147
00:14:07.880 --> 00:14:11.720
Ice is stupid. People standing on ice
are more stupid.

148
00:14:12.920 --> 00:14:16.720
And over there,
when she was falling...

149
00:14:17.040 --> 00:14:18.480
...and my hand grabbed her...

150
00:14:19.560 --> 00:14:23.280
...and I got her arm through that coat,
I could feel it.

151
00:14:24.040 --> 00:14:25.720
Electric.

152
00:14:26.200 --> 00:14:28.560
You said the same thing
last year, Rock.

153
00:14:29.800 --> 00:14:31.000
Did I?

154
00:14:31.160 --> 00:14:33.280
- so you better develop your brain.

155
00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:35.240
- You're left-handed.
- Absolutely.

156
00:14:35.400 --> 00:14:37.600
Come on, Rock. Let's go.

157
00:14:39.920 --> 00:14:43.560
We're done. There's no place
to sit down around here.

158
00:14:43.760 --> 00:14:45.000
It's all right.

159
00:14:45.160 --> 00:14:49.320
It ain't all right! It's depressing
and freaking cold!

160
00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:51.560
What's the matter with you, Paulie?

161
00:14:51.920 --> 00:14:53.960
You're living backwards, Rocko!

162
00:14:54.120 --> 00:14:57.480
Change the channel from yesterday!
Yesterday wasn't so great!

163
00:14:57.640 --> 00:14:59.920
- It was to me.
- Not to me!

164
00:15:01.720 --> 00:15:04.760
You treated her good.
You had the good times.

165
00:15:05.640 --> 00:15:09.000
I treated her bad.
I don't have to think about this.

166
00:15:10.360 --> 00:15:12.440
She always loved you, Paulie.

167
00:15:16.560 --> 00:15:19.720
Sorry, Rocko,
I can't do this no more.

168
00:16:29.560 --> 00:16:30.680
Can I help you?

169
00:16:31.080 --> 00:16:33.640
No, no, I used to come down
to this place a long time ago.

170
00:16:33.800 --> 00:16:36.320
I was just looking around.
No big deal.

171
00:16:37.160 --> 00:16:38.320
Can I get you a drink?

172
00:16:40.200 --> 00:16:43.400
- All right. Maybe just a short beer.
- Okay.

173
00:16:51.920 --> 00:16:53.640
Go. Go on.

174
00:16:54.600 --> 00:16:56.360
Yeah, go on.
Get him to buy a round.

175
00:16:56.520 --> 00:16:58.320
Get him to buy a round. Go.

176
00:16:58.680 --> 00:17:01.440
Get him to... He's got it.
He's spending money.

177
00:17:01.600 --> 00:17:06.600
Listen, I don't mean to cross the line
or anything...

178
00:17:06.760 --> 00:17:09.600
...but I read about your wife's passing
a few years back.

179
00:17:09.800 --> 00:17:11.280
Yeah, it was woman cancer.

180
00:17:11.440 --> 00:17:14.320
Yeah. I always heard
she was a nice person.

181
00:17:14.480 --> 00:17:16.800
Yeah, the best.

182
00:17:17.800 --> 00:17:20.040
- Do I know you?
- We met a long time ago.

183
00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:21.560
We did?

184
00:17:21.760 --> 00:17:24.160
When I was a kid,
you walked me home.

185
00:17:24.320 --> 00:17:27.440
- I did?
- Told me to stop smoking and things.

186
00:17:28.920 --> 00:17:31.040
Stop smoking...

187
00:17:31.680 --> 00:17:35.080
Are you Little Marie that used to
hang out at that Atomic Hoagie shop?

188
00:17:35.240 --> 00:17:37.000
Yeah, that's right.

189
00:17:37.600 --> 00:17:39.880
Yeah, now I remember.
I walked you home.

190
00:17:40.040 --> 00:17:43.760
When you got there, you turned
around and said, "Screw you, creepo."

191
00:17:43.920 --> 00:17:46.120
- I didn't say that.
- Yeah, you did.

192
00:17:46.320 --> 00:17:49.600
- You sure?
- Great insults last a long time.

193
00:17:49.760 --> 00:17:53.000
Yo! Yo, is that you?
Is that really you?

194
00:17:53.520 --> 00:17:55.720
- How you doing?
- I think he wants to drink alone.

195
00:17:55.960 --> 00:17:58.800
Well, then give him his drink, then.
I ain't stopping you.

196
00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:02.320
What's that, your man or something?
No, I don't think so.

197
00:18:05.040 --> 00:18:08.200
Anyway, me and my friends,
we're right down there.

198
00:18:08.400 --> 00:18:11.560
Think you could buy us a round?
You got the money. Just one round.

199
00:18:11.720 --> 00:18:14.480
Hey. Thank you.

200
00:18:14.640 --> 00:18:17.640
What are you doing
pushing my hand away like that?

201
00:18:17.800 --> 00:18:20.080
- What's your name?
- Angie. What do you wanna know for?

202
00:18:20.240 --> 00:18:23.120
- Don't be playing a fool for that guy.
- A fool?

203
00:18:23.280 --> 00:18:24.400
- Yeah.
- A fool?

204
00:18:24.560 --> 00:18:27.440
I'm the fool? You're the fool, not me!

205
00:18:27.600 --> 00:18:30.480
You got it twisted. You're the fool.
I'm a person, just like you.

206
00:18:30.680 --> 00:18:34.120
You ain't no better than me. You think
you're a big shot now? You're nothing.

207
00:18:34.280 --> 00:18:37.960
You ain't no better than me.
No better!

208
00:18:39.520 --> 00:18:40.760
Glad you dropped in?

209
00:18:40.920 --> 00:18:43.480
I think the neighborhood
is changing a little.

210
00:18:44.320 --> 00:18:46.920
- What was that all about?
- I don't know. Forget about it.

211
00:18:47.120 --> 00:18:50.200
I'm gonna lock up, so if you wanna
take off, I'll tally everything up.

212
00:18:50.360 --> 00:18:51.920
- Yeah, thanks.
- How you doing, Rock?

213
00:18:52.080 --> 00:18:53.640
I'm good, thanks.

214
00:18:56.080 --> 00:18:58.760
- You live around here?
- About eight blocks from here.

215
00:18:59.920 --> 00:19:01.640
Eight blocks.

216
00:19:02.800 --> 00:19:04.480
You need a lift?

217
00:19:04.920 --> 00:19:06.880
All right.

218
00:19:07.040 --> 00:19:08.760
Did you ever get married?

219
00:19:08.920 --> 00:19:10.640
- Yeah, sort of.
- Sort of?

220
00:19:10.800 --> 00:19:13.200
- Yeah, well, he took off.
- Poof, just like that?

221
00:19:13.360 --> 00:19:15.400
Yeah, just like that.

222
00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:18.600
- You sort of have any kids?
- Yeah, I got one kid.

223
00:19:18.800 --> 00:19:22.280
Yeah? Me too. Me too.
Wonderful boy.

224
00:19:22.440 --> 00:19:25.960
Hey, tough guy! What's the matter,
you can't buy a round?

225
00:19:26.120 --> 00:19:28.560
The girl was being nice
to your dumb ass.

226
00:19:28.720 --> 00:19:31.280
- What you doing with that pig?
- Think you can disrespect us?

227
00:19:31.440 --> 00:19:34.240
- She ain't nothing but a jealous bitch!
- Come on back!

228
00:19:34.600 --> 00:19:36.280
Hey, don't listen to them.

229
00:19:36.440 --> 00:19:39.360
Both of youse,
you ain't no better than me.

230
00:19:39.520 --> 00:19:42.640
Come over here, you'll get
your head kicked in around here.

231
00:19:42.800 --> 00:19:46.720
- You punch-drunk, goofy bastard.
- You ain't no big shot, look at you.

232
00:19:46.880 --> 00:19:50.640
You ain't even got a car
to take that pig home.

233
00:19:53.240 --> 00:19:54.480
You all right?

234
00:19:55.960 --> 00:19:56.920
Yeah.

235
00:19:59.440 --> 00:20:02.120
What are you doing?
Don't get out. It's all right.

236
00:20:04.840 --> 00:20:07.880
No, Little Marie. It ain't all right.

237
00:20:12.480 --> 00:20:14.160
- Yo.
- What?

238
00:20:14.360 --> 00:20:16.240
I'll tell you what. Get inside.

239
00:20:16.400 --> 00:20:19.320
- You get inside. Yeah, you.
- Hey, leave him alone!

240
00:20:19.480 --> 00:20:20.680
- Yo, man!
- See it?

241
00:20:20.840 --> 00:20:22.920
- You see that? You see that?
- Yeah. All right.

242
00:20:23.120 --> 00:20:25.320
- What do you say?
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry!

243
00:20:25.520 --> 00:20:27.080
Get a job!

244
00:20:42.480 --> 00:20:44.400
That guy sends his apologies.

245
00:20:45.200 --> 00:20:46.640
Okay.

246
00:21:02.760 --> 00:21:06.960
Martin. Martin. Yo, Martin!

247
00:21:11.600 --> 00:21:13.400
I see you still got your key.

248
00:21:13.560 --> 00:21:15.400
Yeah, I got a key.
You got time to talk?

249
00:21:16.080 --> 00:21:18.640
I got a lot of time
since your people let me go.

250
00:21:18.800 --> 00:21:21.000
You know I had
nothing to do with that.

251
00:21:21.200 --> 00:21:22.640
Yeah.

252
00:21:24.240 --> 00:21:26.200
Yeah, we moved in
about a year ago.

253
00:21:26.360 --> 00:21:28.600
- Yeah?
- Yeah, I mean, it's only temporary.

254
00:21:28.760 --> 00:21:31.560
- Yeah, I could see that.
- I'm gonna look for an apartment.

255
00:21:31.720 --> 00:21:33.240
Apartments are nice.

256
00:21:33.400 --> 00:21:35.080
Yeah. It is what it is, you know.

257
00:21:35.240 --> 00:21:37.040
Yeah, it is what it is.

258
00:21:37.200 --> 00:21:40.280
This place used to be pretty nice.
There's a lot of history around here.

259
00:21:40.440 --> 00:21:41.920
- Yeah.
- Like down the street...

260
00:21:42.080 --> 00:21:43.600
...is the Cambria Fight Club.

261
00:21:43.760 --> 00:21:45.560
They used to call it
the Bucket of Blood.

262
00:21:45.720 --> 00:21:48.840
I took some massive beatings there.
But it was nice. Good memories.

263
00:21:49.040 --> 00:21:53.880
And I heard these buildings are like,
I don't know, 100, 150 years old.

264
00:21:54.040 --> 00:21:58.920
If I was 150 years old, I'd be falling
apart too. So it's okay, building.

265
00:21:59.080 --> 00:22:00.240
Does that light work?

266
00:22:00.400 --> 00:22:02.640
- No, it's burnt out or something. Yeah.
- Yeah?

267
00:22:05.160 --> 00:22:09.360
Listen, thanks for the ride,
and I'm sorry about those guys.

268
00:22:09.520 --> 00:22:12.960
Some of those guys just got their
brains on backwards and stuff.

269
00:22:13.120 --> 00:22:15.880
- What's he doing out so late?
- Is that your kid?

270
00:22:16.040 --> 00:22:18.080
Yeah. Wish he wouldn't
stay out so late.

271
00:22:18.360 --> 00:22:21.040
- Amazing.
- Yeah, what's that?

272
00:22:21.640 --> 00:22:23.880
Last time I seen you,
you was a kid...

273
00:22:24.040 --> 00:22:26.120
...and now you officially
got one of your own.

274
00:22:26.280 --> 00:22:27.320
It's amazing.

275
00:22:27.480 --> 00:22:31.400
You know, he sort of resembles you.
He's got that big Irish hair.

276
00:22:32.240 --> 00:22:33.480
Yeah, it's the other one.

277
00:22:36.800 --> 00:22:39.080
- Yeah?
- His father was from Jamaica.

278
00:22:39.280 --> 00:22:40.520
Jamaica? European.

279
00:22:43.440 --> 00:22:45.760
Was you on a cruise ship
or something?

280
00:22:45.920 --> 00:22:47.760
- No, not really.
- What's his name?

281
00:22:47.920 --> 00:22:52.360
- Steps. Short for Stevenson.
- Makes sense.

282
00:22:55.760 --> 00:22:58.760
Does he look mad at me, or is it
maybe the angle I'm standing at?

283
00:22:58.960 --> 00:23:01.480
No. He's a good kid.

284
00:23:01.640 --> 00:23:03.960
- You wanna meet him?
- It's getting kind of late.

285
00:23:04.120 --> 00:23:07.560
- I got so many things to do.
- Yeah, yeah, I understand.

286
00:23:08.400 --> 00:23:12.200
Thanks again for the ride
and everything else.

287
00:23:14.160 --> 00:23:15.640
I'll see you.

288
00:23:16.720 --> 00:23:18.120
You too.

289
00:23:18.280 --> 00:23:22.040
Hey, Steps, come on. Let's go.
Say good night to your friend.

290
00:23:22.280 --> 00:23:24.600
What are you doing out
in the cold with no hat on?

291
00:23:24.760 --> 00:23:27.040
- Did you get something to eat?
- Yeah, I already ate.

292
00:23:27.200 --> 00:23:28.720
All right.

293
00:23:28.880 --> 00:23:31.120
- You're late, you know.
- I can take care of myself.

294
00:23:31.920 --> 00:23:33.800
Yo, Little Marie!

295
00:23:34.920 --> 00:23:36.800
Ain't you gonna
introduce me to your kid?

296
00:23:36.960 --> 00:23:39.080
- How you doing, Steps?
- What's up?

297
00:23:39.280 --> 00:23:44.240
Listen, I got this place, this restaurant,
nice little eatery not too far from here.

298
00:23:44.400 --> 00:23:46.320
What's all this junk? Got a tissue.

299
00:23:46.480 --> 00:23:49.960
Sometimes I feel like a kangaroo,
all the stuff in my pocket, you know.

300
00:23:50.160 --> 00:23:52.200
Here you go.
I got a card, there it is.

301
00:23:52.360 --> 00:23:54.320
And if you ever get a chance,
it'd be great...

302
00:23:54.480 --> 00:23:57.200
...if both of youse
come down there and eat.

303
00:23:57.360 --> 00:24:02.960
It'd be great, free. You know.
Anyway, I'll leave it over there... Here.

304
00:24:04.120 --> 00:24:07.520
I'll leave it on the steps. Steps.

305
00:24:10.920 --> 00:24:12.600
See you later.

306
00:24:14.560 --> 00:24:16.360
Come on, let's go.

307
00:24:18.800 --> 00:24:21.000
<i>You've known what's best for you
since you were 10.</i>

308
00:24:21.160 --> 00:24:23.080
Since you walked in here alone.

309
00:24:24.040 --> 00:24:26.400
Got everything money can buy...

310
00:24:26.560 --> 00:24:28.520
...except what it can't.

311
00:24:29.320 --> 00:24:33.120
It's pride. Pride is what got
your ass out of here.

312
00:24:34.600 --> 00:24:36.360
Losing is what brung you back.

313
00:24:37.880 --> 00:24:42.440
But people like you, they need
to be tested. Need a challenge.

314
00:24:42.640 --> 00:24:44.760
That ain't gonna happen.
Ain't nothing out there.

315
00:24:45.080 --> 00:24:48.360
There's always somebody
out there. Always.

316
00:24:48.800 --> 00:24:50.960
When that time comes
and you find something...

317
00:24:51.120 --> 00:24:53.520
...standing in front of you
that ain't running...

318
00:24:53.680 --> 00:24:58.800
...that ain't backing up, hitting on you,
and you're too damn tired to breathe...

319
00:24:59.160 --> 00:25:02.000
You find that situation on you,
that's good.

320
00:25:02.160 --> 00:25:04.600
Because that's baptism under fire.

321
00:25:06.600 --> 00:25:09.160
You get through that,
you find the only kind of respect...

322
00:25:09.360 --> 00:25:10.920
...that matters in this damn world:

323
00:25:11.120 --> 00:25:13.160
Self-respect.

324
00:25:15.600 --> 00:25:18.360
Thanks, Martin. I appreciate that.

325
00:25:18.520 --> 00:25:20.200
Now, what can the champ
do for you?

326
00:25:21.520 --> 00:25:24.040
You can give me
some of that money you got.

327
00:25:25.240 --> 00:25:27.720
- You know, I like you, Martin.
- But not that much.

328
00:25:28.760 --> 00:25:30.680
Exactly.

329
00:25:34.320 --> 00:25:36.440
How about a picture with the kid?
All right?

330
00:25:36.600 --> 00:25:37.960
Sure.

331
00:25:39.800 --> 00:25:42.480
Here, son, hold up your fist.
Makes you look more hazardous.

332
00:25:45.040 --> 00:25:46.280
- There you go.
- Thanks, Rock.

333
00:25:46.440 --> 00:25:48.200
Enjoy your meal.

334
00:25:49.040 --> 00:25:50.560
- He's a nice guy, isn't he?
- Rocky?

335
00:25:50.720 --> 00:25:52.760
- Yeah.
- Spider just went downstairs.

336
00:25:52.920 --> 00:25:55.280
- I don't know if that's all right.
- What's he doing?

337
00:25:55.440 --> 00:25:57.640
I don't know. That's your friend.

338
00:26:03.480 --> 00:26:04.840
Yo, Spider!

339
00:26:05.040 --> 00:26:08.440
- Let me do some dishes. I feel better.
- Come on. You're my guest.

340
00:26:08.600 --> 00:26:11.000
- Let me do something.
- Keep eating. Guests do that.

341
00:26:11.160 --> 00:26:13.480
Don't make me fight you again.
Last time you got lucky.

342
00:26:13.920 --> 00:26:15.880
Lucky? Okay.

343
00:26:16.080 --> 00:26:17.640
Jesus wants me to work.

344
00:26:18.320 --> 00:26:20.680
- Yo, Rocky.
- Yeah?

345
00:26:20.840 --> 00:26:21.880
You've got guests.

346
00:26:24.400 --> 00:26:26.080
Don't get too wet, okay?

347
00:26:27.440 --> 00:26:29.160
Glad Jesus didn't ask you to cook.

348
00:26:35.280 --> 00:26:36.880
You kept the card.

349
00:26:37.040 --> 00:26:38.800
Yeah, I kept the card.

350
00:26:38.960 --> 00:26:41.200
- Why don't you sit down?
- Yeah, sure.

351
00:26:50.400 --> 00:26:54.760
Because, you know what, I walk in
there, I say good morning, I do this:

352
00:26:55.360 --> 00:26:56.560
<i>Tonight, boxing once again.</i>

353
00:26:56.720 --> 00:26:59.400
<i>Two contrasting styles
in almost every way.</i>

354
00:26:59.560 --> 00:27:02.760
Hey, can you turn this up?
Turn this up, please.

355
00:27:02.920 --> 00:27:06.120
<i>Who was the best of all time?
If two athletes from different eras...</i>

356
00:27:06.320 --> 00:27:09.360
<i>... could compete against one another,
who would come out on top?</i>

357
00:27:09.520 --> 00:27:13.160
<i>Given the same rules, using the same
equipment, who was the greatest?</i>

358
00:27:13.360 --> 00:27:15.080
<i>We feed our facts
into the computer.</i>

359
00:27:15.280 --> 00:27:17.560
<i>They weigh in on who they
think will reign supreme...</i>

360
00:27:17.720 --> 00:27:20.720
<i>... while fielding the comments of our
illustrious panel of sportswriters.</i>

361
00:27:26.280 --> 00:27:27.840
Champ!

362
00:27:29.360 --> 00:27:30.760
- Yo, champ!
- Yeah?

363
00:27:30.920 --> 00:27:33.720
Come check out this trash
they're talking about you, man!

364
00:27:33.880 --> 00:27:36.720
- What you talking about?
- Come check this out. Hurry up.

365
00:27:37.000 --> 00:27:39.240
<i>Tonight, the former two-time
heavyweight champion...</i>

366
00:27:39.440 --> 00:27:41.360
<i>... from Philadelphia, Rocky Balboa.</i>

367
00:27:41.520 --> 00:27:43.440
<i>All right, Chuck Johnson,
USA Today?</i>

368
00:27:43.600 --> 00:27:46.240
<i>There's no question that
Rocky Balboa fought tougher fights...</i>

369
00:27:46.400 --> 00:27:47.880
<i>... during a tougher era in boxing.</i>

370
00:27:48.080 --> 00:27:49.800
<i>You look at Mason Dixon
in his career...</i>

371
00:27:50.000 --> 00:27:52.200
<i>... he's basically been
spoon-fed his opponents.</i>

372
00:27:52.360 --> 00:27:54.440
<i>No question in my mind.
Not only does Rocky win...</i>

373
00:27:54.640 --> 00:27:55.880
<i>... but he wins knockout.</i>

374
00:27:57.880 --> 00:27:59.440
Rocky!

375
00:28:00.760 --> 00:28:01.720
Offspring.

376
00:28:02.960 --> 00:28:03.960
<i>Bernard Fernandez?</i>

377
00:28:04.120 --> 00:28:05.800
<i>Dixon is a victim
of his own dominance.</i>

378
00:28:06.000 --> 00:28:08.920
<i>He's never been in
real knockdown-dragout brawls.</i>

379
00:28:09.080 --> 00:28:10.760
<i>He never had to dig down
to rally back.</i>

380
00:28:11.240 --> 00:28:13.040
<i>If he tries to dig down
against Balboa...</i>

381
00:28:13.200 --> 00:28:15.560
<i>... he'll find he doesn't have
a big enough shovel.</i>

382
00:28:15.720 --> 00:28:18.440
<i>I clearly give it to Balboa.</i>

383
00:28:18.640 --> 00:28:21.720
What happened to you?
What happened to you?

384
00:28:21.880 --> 00:28:24.200
<i>Boxing historian
Burt Randolph Sugar.</i>

385
00:28:24.360 --> 00:28:27.400
<i>Dixon has fought cream puffs.
We don't know what he's made of.</i>

386
00:28:27.600 --> 00:28:29.640
<i>But both in their primes,
you gotta factor in...</i>

387
00:28:29.800 --> 00:28:31.600
<i>... Dixon's unbelievable speed...</i>

388
00:28:31.760 --> 00:28:34.280
<i>... his slashing offense.
He cuts Balboa to bits.</i>

389
00:28:34.480 --> 00:28:37.160
<i>No doubt. Dixon wins all the way.</i>

390
00:28:38.440 --> 00:28:42.680
<i>Here's where our subjectivity ends.
Let's see what the computer says.</i>

391
00:28:42.840 --> 00:28:47.400
<i>Dixon unloads on Balboa. Rocky has
no answer. Balboa is eating jabs.</i>

392
00:28:48.400 --> 00:28:50.120
- What time is it?
- Mason time.

393
00:28:50.320 --> 00:28:52.840
- What time is it?
- Mason time.

394
00:28:53.000 --> 00:28:55.080
- What time is it?
- Mason time.

395
00:29:03.120 --> 00:29:07.360
<i>Now Dixon is done. He is reeling.
He is almost out on his feet!</i>

396
00:29:07.560 --> 00:29:09.960
<i>Balboa turning up the heat.
Pounds him across the ring.</i>

397
00:29:10.160 --> 00:29:13.720
<i>Boy, he's bit off more than he
can chew this time. Believe it.</i>

398
00:29:13.880 --> 00:29:17.080
<i>Oh, a murderous right hook!
And Dixon is out on his feet.</i>

399
00:29:17.480 --> 00:29:20.520
<i>He is out cold as he
crumbles to the canvas.</i>

400
00:29:20.680 --> 00:29:24.720
<i>And it is Balboa who has won...</i>

401
00:29:25.800 --> 00:29:28.480
Ladies and gentlemen, Baby Rocky.
Baby Rocky.

402
00:29:34.720 --> 00:29:38.960
I'm glad you liked the food. If you heat
that up, it's pretty good in the morning.

403
00:29:40.200 --> 00:29:41.600
Yeah, thanks, man.

404
00:29:42.120 --> 00:29:45.640
Nice kid. I hope this music ain't giving
you a headache. I like this old stuff.

405
00:29:45.840 --> 00:29:47.880
No, I like it. It's nice.

406
00:29:48.320 --> 00:29:50.280
Well, good. Good.

407
00:29:59.280 --> 00:30:03.360
Yo, you think Steps wants a job?
Make a few bucks on the weekend?

408
00:30:03.520 --> 00:30:07.000
It's good making your own G's. My kid
stashed a few bucks doing that.

409
00:30:07.560 --> 00:30:09.200
Why are you being so nice?

410
00:30:10.400 --> 00:30:12.520
I don't want you to think
nothing's off, you know.

411
00:30:12.680 --> 00:30:15.720
My wife, she's gone, but she ain't.
You know what I mean?

412
00:30:15.880 --> 00:30:17.880
Yeah, well, I wasn't thinking that.
Believe me.

413
00:30:18.040 --> 00:30:20.560
- No? Then what was you thinking?
- No.

414
00:30:20.720 --> 00:30:23.080
That you don't owe us nothing.
What are you doing?

415
00:30:23.240 --> 00:30:24.880
Be patient.

416
00:30:25.040 --> 00:30:26.480
Now...

417
00:30:27.000 --> 00:30:30.800
...I don't owe you nothing,
but why do you gotta...

418
00:30:30.960 --> 00:30:34.440
...owe something to get...?

419
00:30:35.360 --> 00:30:36.520
Bingo.

420
00:30:41.640 --> 00:30:45.800
Why do you gotta owe something
to get something, you know? Really.

421
00:30:48.560 --> 00:30:52.120
I think hanging out with your kid
would be nice. What do you think?

422
00:30:52.280 --> 00:30:54.400
I think that'd be nice.

423
00:30:55.440 --> 00:30:58.720
Good. That's very nice.

424
00:30:58.880 --> 00:31:01.000
I'm glad you come by.

425
00:31:01.440 --> 00:31:04.600
It was nice watching you eat.

426
00:31:06.440 --> 00:31:08.160
Good company.

427
00:31:11.080 --> 00:31:13.520
Yo, Little Marie. Let there be light!

428
00:31:24.120 --> 00:31:26.080
- You like dogs?
- Dogs?

429
00:31:26.280 --> 00:31:30.760
Dogs. This is like a dog pound.
It's where they keep...

430
00:31:31.200 --> 00:31:35.720
...a large variety of dogs. I used to
come here all the time for sightseeing.

431
00:31:35.880 --> 00:31:39.160
But, you know,
you learn a lot talking to dogs.

432
00:31:39.320 --> 00:31:42.640
- Really, you do.
- Yeah, man. So...

433
00:31:42.800 --> 00:31:45.200
Hey, man, how about this one?

434
00:31:46.800 --> 00:31:48.440
He don't look too friendly, my friend.

435
00:31:48.600 --> 00:31:51.200
Man, this is the one.
Hey, boy, how you doing?

436
00:31:51.360 --> 00:31:54.480
Hey, what about this one here?
Come here, boy.

437
00:31:54.640 --> 00:31:56.080
- Who, him?
- Yeah, why not?

438
00:31:56.240 --> 00:31:58.320
Hell, no. That is one ugly dog, man.

439
00:31:58.480 --> 00:32:02.640
I know, but it's kind of a cute ugly.
If you look at it closely, the color...

440
00:32:02.800 --> 00:32:06.480
...it looks like old furniture, like some
kind of pirate-chest thing going on.

441
00:32:06.640 --> 00:32:09.000
Yeah, sure, man.
Hey, so how about a young one?

442
00:32:09.160 --> 00:32:12.480
Steps, forget him. Come over here.
I want you to see something.

443
00:32:12.680 --> 00:32:16.840
Now, you notice what this animal
is doing here? Lying in that position?

444
00:32:17.040 --> 00:32:18.200
He ain't doing nothing.

445
00:32:18.360 --> 00:32:21.000
No, he's doing a lot.
He ain't wasting no energy.

446
00:32:21.160 --> 00:32:22.280
Because he's dead.

447
00:32:28.280 --> 00:32:31.080
He ain't dead. There's a lot of
good mileage left on that animal.

448
00:32:31.240 --> 00:32:35.120
Good food, the addition of a couple
of new friends, bingo, he's back.

449
00:32:35.280 --> 00:32:38.600
- What do you think is a good name?
- It's your dog. You name him.

450
00:32:38.760 --> 00:32:41.240
No. It's, like,
a community animal. Fifty-fifty.

451
00:32:41.400 --> 00:32:43.760
Look, I don't know much
about no dogs.

452
00:32:43.920 --> 00:32:45.480
Well, it ain't that complicated.

453
00:32:45.680 --> 00:32:49.120
You pet him, you feed him,
and nature takes its course.

454
00:32:49.320 --> 00:32:52.040
You know, so...
Don't you wanna name an animal?

455
00:32:52.200 --> 00:32:56.040
Every guy should at one time
try to name an animal something.

456
00:32:56.560 --> 00:32:57.920
I don't know. Fleabag?

457
00:32:58.680 --> 00:33:02.600
It's catchy. It ain't original,
but it's pretty good.

458
00:33:02.760 --> 00:33:05.040
I think you could come up with,
in your young brain...

459
00:33:05.200 --> 00:33:08.080
...something better to throw out
than Fleabag.

460
00:33:08.880 --> 00:33:10.640
Punchy. How's that?

461
00:33:12.080 --> 00:33:14.400
