524
00:36:59.960 --> 00:37:02.280
<i>Let's go back to Sunday's race...</i>

525
00:37:02.440 --> 00:37:04.040
Hey, hey, hey, cheer up.

526
00:37:04.200 --> 00:37:07.560
It's free advertisement.
Come on. Meat house calls.

527
00:37:17.200 --> 00:37:18.920
Yo, Robert.

528
00:37:21.360 --> 00:37:22.880
What are you doing out so late?

529
00:37:23.040 --> 00:37:25.480
I tried calling,
but nothing was picking up.

530
00:37:25.680 --> 00:37:27.800
- Is something wrong?
- I just wanted to come by...

531
00:37:27.960 --> 00:37:29.880
...and see you in person.
- Wanna come inside?

532
00:37:30.040 --> 00:37:32.720
No. I just wanna get
your opinion on something.

533
00:37:33.360 --> 00:37:34.760
Sure. Opinion on what?

534
00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:37.160
You know, they say you only
go around once, right?

535
00:37:37.360 --> 00:37:39.480
- Yeah, I've heard that.
- Well...

536
00:37:39.640 --> 00:37:42.040
...I think I wanna, like,
do something.

537
00:37:42.200 --> 00:37:45.000
- Like what?
- Fight.

538
00:37:45.760 --> 00:37:49.200
You know, nothing big.
Small stuff, like locally. You know.

539
00:37:51.040 --> 00:37:53.760
Don't you think you're too,
you know, old?

540
00:37:54.280 --> 00:37:56.120
You think you ought to
stop trying things...

541
00:37:56.280 --> 00:37:58.640
...because you had a few
too many birthdays? I do not.

542
00:37:58.800 --> 00:38:00.200
People will think you're crazy.

543
00:38:00.360 --> 00:38:04.080
What's crazy about standing
toe to toe saying, "I am," you know?

544
00:38:04.360 --> 00:38:05.800
That's just ego talking.

545
00:38:07.280 --> 00:38:09.840
What are you trying to prove
to other people, Pop?

546
00:38:10.800 --> 00:38:13.200
Prove? Listen, I stopped thinking...

547
00:38:13.360 --> 00:38:15.400
...the way other people think
a long time ago.

548
00:38:15.560 --> 00:38:17.160
You gotta think like you think.

549
00:38:18.960 --> 00:38:22.520
- I do.
- Do you? Good.

550
00:38:22.680 --> 00:38:27.040
You gotta face reality, okay?
It's a different world now.

551
00:38:27.920 --> 00:38:30.160
Only the clothes is different.

552
00:38:32.080 --> 00:38:34.960
I really don't know
what you want from me.

553
00:38:35.320 --> 00:38:40.080
I just wanted us to get involved.
You know, like, home team.

554
00:38:42.040 --> 00:38:47.280
Look, whatever it is, whatever
you're going through, it'll pass.

555
00:38:47.480 --> 00:38:49.400
Yeah, you're probably right.

556
00:38:49.560 --> 00:38:52.000
Time is gonna catch up to all of us.

557
00:38:52.240 --> 00:38:55.400
- Especially if you're standing still.
- Hey, come on.

558
00:38:58.160 --> 00:39:00.360
Look, I'm gonna call you
in the morning.

559
00:39:03.160 --> 00:39:05.520
<i>- Did you tell this to your kid?
- Yeah, I did.</i>

560
00:39:05.680 --> 00:39:07.760
<i>- What'd he think, you're nuts, right?
- Yeah.</i>

561
00:39:07.920 --> 00:39:13.440
Oh, well, he don't believe in you?
Welcome to my world, buddy.

562
00:39:13.600 --> 00:39:16.680
Rocko, nobody's giving you
no title shot.

563
00:39:16.880 --> 00:39:19.160
I know that. I don't want one.

564
00:39:19.320 --> 00:39:21.640
So this isn't a mental disturbance?

565
00:39:22.760 --> 00:39:24.040
No.

566
00:39:24.240 --> 00:39:27.120
You're mad because
they took down your statue?

567
00:39:27.720 --> 00:39:29.480
No.

568
00:39:30.280 --> 00:39:31.760
Not really, no.

569
00:39:31.960 --> 00:39:36.840
If it's about money, just hang a sign
around your neck saying, "Punch me."

570
00:39:37.040 --> 00:39:39.880
Five dollars, you'll make big money.

571
00:39:41.520 --> 00:39:43.840
What? You haven't peaked yet?

572
00:39:44.720 --> 00:39:47.000
- Peaked?
- Yeah, peaked.

573
00:39:47.440 --> 00:39:49.800
I don't know. There's still
some stuff in the basement.

574
00:39:50.840 --> 00:39:53.480
- What basement?
- In here.

575
00:39:54.280 --> 00:39:55.880
Tell me about the stuff.

576
00:39:57.120 --> 00:40:00.400
- What about it?
- Tell me about the stuff inside.

577
00:40:00.560 --> 00:40:02.920
- Is it angry?
- Angry?

578
00:40:03.080 --> 00:40:05.080
Are you mad because
Adrian left you?

579
00:40:05.240 --> 00:40:07.720
She didn't leave, Paulie. She died.

580
00:40:07.920 --> 00:40:09.640
Okay. Okay, okay, okay.

581
00:40:13.960 --> 00:40:17.520
You know, sometimes
it's hard to breathe.

582
00:40:17.680 --> 00:40:21.280
You know, I feel, like,
this beast inside me.

583
00:40:21.560 --> 00:40:24.120
It's okay, Rocko. Please, it's okay.

584
00:40:24.280 --> 00:40:27.560
Is it okay?

585
00:40:32.680 --> 00:40:36.120
I just never knew it was
supposed to be this hard.

586
00:40:36.280 --> 00:40:39.120
It wasn't supposed to be like this,
Paulie. You know, it...

587
00:40:48.720 --> 00:40:50.760
So you wanna come by
and help me train?

588
00:40:50.960 --> 00:40:52.320
I got a job here.

589
00:40:52.720 --> 00:40:54.240
I understand.

590
00:40:54.640 --> 00:40:57.400
Remember you said if you stay
one place long enough...

591
00:40:57.560 --> 00:40:58.840
...you become that place?

592
00:40:59.480 --> 00:41:01.640
Rocko, this is all I got.

593
00:41:02.080 --> 00:41:04.480
I understand, Paulie. I do.

594
00:41:08.880 --> 00:41:12.720
If you get time and come down
and see me train, I'd appreciate it.

595
00:41:13.680 --> 00:41:15.560
Of course, Rocko.

596
00:41:18.600 --> 00:41:20.200
Bye, Paulie.

597
00:41:20.440 --> 00:41:20.880
Goodbye, Rocko.

598
00:41:20.880 --> 00:41:22.440
Goodbye, Rocko.

599
00:41:25.000 --> 00:41:26.920
Take care, Rocko.

600
00:41:32.040 --> 00:41:35.520
<i>This plenary session of the
Pennsylvania Athletic Commission...</i>

601
00:41:35.680 --> 00:41:41.000
...is convened in order to consider
the application of Rocky Balboa...

602
00:41:41.200 --> 00:41:45.240
...for the issuance of a discretionary
professional boxing license...

603
00:41:45.400 --> 00:41:50.000
...due to his ineligibility to be
licensed as a matter of right.

604
00:41:50.160 --> 00:41:53.960
Mr. Balboa, you're welcome here.
Since you're representing yourself...

605
00:41:54.160 --> 00:41:57.160
...we invite you to make an opening
statement, if you'd like to.

606
00:41:57.320 --> 00:41:59.760
No, I was just curious how I did,
that's all.

607
00:41:59.920 --> 00:42:04.280
All right, well, the Medical
Advisory Board has informed us...

608
00:42:04.440 --> 00:42:07.240
...that the battery of tests
to which you've been subjected...

609
00:42:07.440 --> 00:42:10.560
...you've passed these tests
with flying colors.

610
00:42:10.800 --> 00:42:13.200
And we congratulate you for that.

611
00:42:13.360 --> 00:42:16.160
- Thanks.
- However, this commission...

612
00:42:16.320 --> 00:42:19.920
...in good conscience,
cannot recommend you for a license...

613
00:42:20.320 --> 00:42:23.400
...and we therefore deny
your application.

614
00:42:24.680 --> 00:42:27.360
- Didn't I do what you asked?
- Yes, you did.

615
00:42:27.520 --> 00:42:29.160
So I should get a license, right?

616
00:42:29.480 --> 00:42:30.600
Not exactly.

617
00:42:33.520 --> 00:42:36.880
So why did you give me all them tests
if you was never passing me?

618
00:42:37.040 --> 00:42:38.960
We've gotta stand by
our decision here...

619
00:42:39.120 --> 00:42:42.320
...and we have to deny your request
for a license at this time.

620
00:42:54.120 --> 00:42:56.600
Yo, don't I got some rights?

621
00:42:56.760 --> 00:42:58.760
What rights do you think
you're referring to?

622
00:42:58.960 --> 00:43:01.480
Like in that official paper
they wrote down the street?

623
00:43:01.680 --> 00:43:03.520
- That's the Bill of Rights.
- Bill of Rights.

624
00:43:03.680 --> 00:43:05.800
Don't it say something about going
after what makes you happy?

625
00:43:06.000 --> 00:43:08.640
No, that's "the pursuit of happiness."
But what's your point?

626
00:43:08.800 --> 00:43:11.920
My point is I'm pursuing something,
and nobody looks too happy about it.

627
00:43:12.240 --> 00:43:14.480
But we're just looking out
for your interests.

628
00:43:14.640 --> 00:43:18.160
I appreciate that, but maybe you're
looking out for your interests more.

629
00:43:18.320 --> 00:43:21.520
You shouldn't ask people to come here
and pay the freight on something.

630
00:43:21.680 --> 00:43:24.720
They pay, it still ain't good enough.
You think that's right?

631
00:43:24.880 --> 00:43:28.040
Maybe you're doing your job, but why
you gotta stop me from doing mine?

632
00:43:28.560 --> 00:43:32.240
If you're willing to go through all the
battling to get where you want to get...

633
00:43:32.400 --> 00:43:34.080
...who's got the right to stop you?

634
00:43:34.240 --> 00:43:37.520
Maybe you got something you never
finished, something you wanna do.

635
00:43:37.680 --> 00:43:39.840
Something you never said
to somebody, something!

636
00:43:40.000 --> 00:43:42.040
And you're told no,
even after you pay your dues.

637
00:43:42.200 --> 00:43:44.680
Who's got the right
to tell you that? Who? Nobody!

638
00:43:44.880 --> 00:43:47.880
It's your right to listen to your gut.
It's nobody's right to say no...

639
00:43:48.080 --> 00:43:51.320
...after you earn the right to be what you
wanna be or do what you wanna do!

640
00:43:55.400 --> 00:43:59.320
The older I get, the more things
I gotta leave behind. That's life.

641
00:43:59.480 --> 00:44:03.880
The only thing I'm asking you guys
to leave on the table is what's right.

642
00:44:20.560 --> 00:44:22.280
Yo! Have you seen
the paper today?

643
00:44:22.480 --> 00:44:24.520
Front row. Front row.

644
00:44:25.800 --> 00:44:26.800
That is so great.

645
00:44:27.000 --> 00:44:29.400
- All right, all right.
- Let's go get some food. Food.

646
00:44:29.560 --> 00:44:33.240
- Let's get a beer. Come on.
- Come on.

647
00:44:33.680 --> 00:44:35.680
The last two pay-per-views
were in the toilet.

648
00:44:35.840 --> 00:44:38.320
You're not making
heavyweight-championship money.

649
00:44:38.480 --> 00:44:40.400
There's a bunch of nobodies
out there, Mase.

650
00:44:40.560 --> 00:44:43.440
I wanna talk to you about an
opportunity we should run with.

651
00:44:43.600 --> 00:44:47.280
Look at me. You heard Rocky Balboa
applied for a license and got one?

652
00:44:47.440 --> 00:44:49.280
- I heard. Forget about him.
- Hear me out.

653
00:44:49.440 --> 00:44:52.680
You want me to fight a guy I can beat
with both hands tied behind my back.

654
00:44:52.840 --> 00:44:56.040
Everybody knows you could beat him
sitting down. That's not what it's about.

655
00:44:56.240 --> 00:44:59.360
It's about making money. We gotta
capitalize on that computer fight.

656
00:44:59.520 --> 00:45:02.120
This could do a million buys.
That's 15, 20 million to you.

657
00:45:02.320 --> 00:45:04.200
- Forget it.
- No one's beating the door down...

658
00:45:04.400 --> 00:45:06.920
...to watch you fight anymore.
- We got guaranteed fights.

659
00:45:07.120 --> 00:45:09.960
You wanna do this now in front
of your friends, we'll do it now.

660
00:45:10.120 --> 00:45:13.440
We got nothing. All the pay-per-view
fights you come up with got rejected.

661
00:45:13.600 --> 00:45:16.960
You know why? They're all bums
out there. Nobody cares about them.

662
00:45:17.360 --> 00:45:20.960
There's no marquee value.
But this Balboa thing is interesting.

663
00:45:21.240 --> 00:45:22.720
- I don't wanna do it.
- Listen to me.

664
00:45:22.920 --> 00:45:26.640
It's a has-been, never-gonna-be world.
Call it nostalgia, whatever you want...

665
00:45:26.800 --> 00:45:29.880
...but people relate to that stuff.
This is a no-lose. It's all good.

666
00:45:30.320 --> 00:45:32.840
- Good for who?
- For you! Not for me! For you!

667
00:45:33.160 --> 00:45:35.960
Maybe you don't understand.
People don't like you no more.

668
00:45:36.120 --> 00:45:39.440
They don't follow you. They're not
supporting you anymore. Understand?

669
00:45:39.600 --> 00:45:41.640
Don't look at me like
I'm messing with your legacy.

670
00:45:41.840 --> 00:45:43.480
Every jock now thinks
they got a legacy.

671
00:45:43.640 --> 00:45:46.440
A legacy is what you get instead
of getting paid. That's a legacy.

672
00:45:46.640 --> 00:45:49.080
- Don't talk to me like I'm stupid.
- I'm not no more.

673
00:45:49.240 --> 00:45:52.640
Everybody knows you could kick
this old man's ass. But you don't.

674
00:45:52.840 --> 00:45:54.760
Leave him with a little
dignity, so they say:

675
00:45:54.960 --> 00:45:58.280
"Mason Dixon's got compassion.
He's a decent guy, he's a nice guy."

676
00:45:58.480 --> 00:46:00.760
You get a whole new audience,
we'll double your money.

677
00:46:00.920 --> 00:46:02.880
You want a new image?
That's how you get it.

678
00:46:03.080 --> 00:46:04.720
To replace the one
that you two made?

679
00:46:04.880 --> 00:46:07.600
Whoa, wait. We made your
world green. You made the rest.

680
00:46:07.760 --> 00:46:09.680
This is you.
You made all this junk happen.

681
00:46:09.840 --> 00:46:11.440
I've had it up to here with this mess.

682
00:46:11.600 --> 00:46:14.000
Time for me to make changes.
I'm going to Martin's gym.

683
00:46:14.160 --> 00:46:15.840
- We'll talk about it.
- Forget this crap.

684
00:46:16.000 --> 00:46:18.280
I want Martin back.
There's nothing to talk about.

685
00:46:28.560 --> 00:46:30.240
- How you doing?
- Hey, what a surprise.

686
00:46:30.400 --> 00:46:32.680
I was driving around
the neighborhood, I thought...

687
00:46:32.880 --> 00:46:35.400
...why not drive by and say hello?
- You wanna come inside?

688
00:46:35.560 --> 00:46:38.440
No, the dog needs some exercise.
You wanna take a little walk?

689
00:46:38.640 --> 00:46:40.920
- Yeah, yeah. All right.
- It's nice outside.

690
00:46:41.080 --> 00:46:43.520
- All right.
- Nice and brisk.

691
00:46:43.720 --> 00:46:44.840
When did you get a dog?

692
00:46:45.040 --> 00:46:47.040
We picked up Punchy
a couple of days back.

693
00:46:47.200 --> 00:46:48.360
- Punchy?
- Yeah.

694
00:46:48.520 --> 00:46:49.680
You named your dog Punchy?

695
00:46:49.840 --> 00:46:51.480
Your kid come up with the name.

696
00:46:51.640 --> 00:46:53.960
Oh, yeah?
I think that's disrespectful.

697
00:46:54.160 --> 00:46:55.840
Oh, no, no. It's fine, really.

698
00:46:56.000 --> 00:46:59.160
No, it's easy to remember
and it's all that, you know.

699
00:46:59.320 --> 00:47:02.200
Listen, what do you think about
coming over to the restaurant?

700
00:47:02.360 --> 00:47:05.280
- What for?
- Well, you know, for, like...

701
00:47:05.440 --> 00:47:08.720
For work. The hostess is gonna
be having a kid. You'd do good.

702
00:47:08.880 --> 00:47:11.320
- I don't know.
- I'm telling you, you'd do so good.

703
00:47:11.480 --> 00:47:13.840
I appreciate what you're doing
for my kid, but I can't.

704
00:47:14.000 --> 00:47:16.360
Hey, listen, I think you'd like it a lot.

705
00:47:16.560 --> 00:47:18.880
It's a nice environment,
it's very pleasant.

706
00:47:19.040 --> 00:47:21.000
Yeah, can we drop it?

707
00:47:23.400 --> 00:47:24.800
What's bothering you?

708
00:47:25.000 --> 00:47:27.120
Nothing. It's all right.
Listen, I gotta get back.

709
00:47:28.520 --> 00:47:30.360
- No, it ain't all right.
- Oh, come on.

710
00:47:30.680 --> 00:47:32.480
- What?
- I'm gonna be the first person...

711
00:47:32.640 --> 00:47:34.960
...people see when they walk in?
- You give out menus.

712
00:47:35.120 --> 00:47:37.800
You say, "Hello, how are you?"
You sit people down.

713
00:47:37.960 --> 00:47:40.120
Look, if I can do it,
anybody can do it.

714
00:47:40.280 --> 00:47:43.400
You could find 10 better people,
a hundred better people for this job.

715
00:47:43.600 --> 00:47:45.320
Give it a try, like two weeks.

716
00:47:45.520 --> 00:47:47.240
I don't wanna try.

717
00:47:47.400 --> 00:47:49.520
- Who put this stuff in your head?
- Nobody.

718
00:47:49.680 --> 00:47:51.600
Well, it just don't
get in there by itself.

719
00:47:55.040 --> 00:47:56.880
Thanks for coming by.

720
00:47:58.720 --> 00:48:03.040
Yo, when was the last time you
went dancing? Has it been a while?

721
00:48:03.200 --> 00:48:05.000
- Why are you asking?
- I'm asking because...

722
00:48:05.160 --> 00:48:08.280
...you dance around these problems,
you might as well dance with me.

723
00:48:08.440 --> 00:48:11.360
I ain't that good,
but I'm better than the average bear.

724
00:48:11.520 --> 00:48:14.080
Where that came from, I don't know.

725
00:48:14.680 --> 00:48:16.080
- You're crazy.
- A little bit.

726
00:48:16.240 --> 00:48:19.400
But the way you're thinking
and talking, it's a little crazy too.

727
00:48:20.240 --> 00:48:23.720
Come on, you deserve better.
Really. Come on over.

728
00:48:23.880 --> 00:48:27.920
I need you to class my place up.
Philly needs you.

729
00:48:28.280 --> 00:48:31.800
And if you say, "Screw you, creepo"
again, I totally understand.

730
00:48:31.960 --> 00:48:34.280
But I'm warning you,
I'm gonna put myself...

731
00:48:34.480 --> 00:48:36.240
...in the middle of the street here...

732
00:48:36.400 --> 00:48:39.240
...and stand here, me and Punchy,
and wave to the first bus, say:

733
00:48:39.400 --> 00:48:41.040
"Come on over here and mash me!

734
00:48:41.200 --> 00:48:43.560
Little Marie turned down
the job at the restaurant.

735
00:48:43.760 --> 00:48:45.360
She thinks she's better than us."

736
00:48:45.520 --> 00:48:48.680
Oh, yeah? Well, there hasn't been
a bus down here in 20 years.

737
00:48:49.280 --> 00:48:51.200
- Yeah?
- No.

738
00:48:53.200 --> 00:48:54.760
That was a close call.

739
00:48:55.760 --> 00:49:00.560
Listen, seriously. Come on over.
It'd be nice.

740
00:49:03.120 --> 00:49:04.480
All right.

741
00:49:22.000 --> 00:49:23.480
Paulie!

742
00:49:26.680 --> 00:49:28.400
Sorry, Paulie.

743
00:49:29.760 --> 00:49:31.400
Sorry.

744
00:50:01.360 --> 00:50:04.360
How are you?
Get my unusual up there.

745
00:50:04.560 --> 00:50:07.200
Excuse me.
Deliveries are in the back.

746
00:50:07.360 --> 00:50:09.000
I'm not a delivery guy.

747
00:50:09.160 --> 00:50:10.880
Well, do you have a reservation?

748
00:50:11.040 --> 00:50:13.640
Do I look like a freaking Indian?

749
00:50:16.520 --> 00:50:18.720
Hey, Rock? Rocky?

750
00:50:23.440 --> 00:50:26.080
I think we've got a little bit
of a problem with this guy.

751
00:50:26.240 --> 00:50:28.480
Problem?
No, no, he's just a relative.

752
00:50:28.640 --> 00:50:30.800
Oh, okay.

753
00:50:33.240 --> 00:50:34.600
Yo, Paulie.

754
00:50:36.800 --> 00:50:38.720
- What happened to your eye?
- I hit it.

755
00:50:39.000 --> 00:50:40.720
- Why?
- Needed to.

756
00:50:41.360 --> 00:50:42.600
What happened?

757
00:50:42.800 --> 00:50:45.400
- I'm celebrating, Rock.
- Why?

758
00:50:45.560 --> 00:50:47.880
- I retired.
- Retired?

759
00:50:53.520 --> 00:50:56.000
So when did they start
giving retired people meat...

760
00:50:56.160 --> 00:50:58.240
...instead of watches, Paulie?

761
00:51:00.920 --> 00:51:02.800
I don't need a watch.

762
00:51:04.560 --> 00:51:07.840
I got a watch! You gave me a watch!

763
00:51:08.040 --> 00:51:09.240
Paulie...

764
00:51:09.400 --> 00:51:11.840
I don't need no goddamn watch.

765
00:51:13.400 --> 00:51:16.400
- Yo, Paulie.
- I got a watch!

766
00:51:17.680 --> 00:51:19.560
I got two watches!

767
00:51:20.040 --> 00:51:22.120
Yo, Paulie!

768
00:51:33.960 --> 00:51:34.920
Yo, Paulie.

769
00:51:36.520 --> 00:51:37.920
Rock.

770
00:51:38.240 --> 00:51:42.440
It takes guts climbing back in that ring,
knowing you're gonna take a beating.

771
00:51:45.040 --> 00:51:46.880
You're gonna do all right, Rocko.

772
00:51:47.120 --> 00:51:48.400
How do you know that?

773
00:51:50.240 --> 00:51:52.680
The stuff in the basement.

774
00:52:03.240 --> 00:52:04.880
Thanks, Paulie.

775
00:52:09.480 --> 00:52:12.280
- Hey.
- Hey, Rock, how are you?

776
00:52:13.600 --> 00:52:15.640
- You okay?
- Yeah, good. How are you?

777
00:52:15.800 --> 00:52:17.360
- Yeah, fine. This is great.
- Good.

778
00:52:17.520 --> 00:52:20.080
Listen, some guys over there
wanna talk to you.

779
00:52:20.240 --> 00:52:22.920
- Okay. You got it.
- Okay?

780
00:52:26.240 --> 00:52:28.840
- Thanks for coming by. I appreciate it.
- Our pleasure.

781
00:52:29.000 --> 00:52:30.880
- Wanna hear stories?
- What kind of stories?

782
00:52:31.120 --> 00:52:33.680
Well, a lot of people like to hear
these old fight stories.

783
00:52:33.840 --> 00:52:35.240
- Maybe later.
- Okay.

784
00:52:35.400 --> 00:52:39.680
I'm Lou DiBella. This is L.C. Luco.
He's Mason Dixon's manager.

785
00:52:39.920 --> 00:52:42.200
- Will you sit down and join us?
- Sure.

786
00:52:43.720 --> 00:52:46.400
You know, we have the promotional
contract for Mason Dixon...

787
00:52:46.560 --> 00:52:48.000
...who's a big fan.
- Really?

788
00:52:48.200 --> 00:52:50.240
When he heard you were
interested in fighting...

789
00:52:50.400 --> 00:52:52.520
...he thought why not try
to work something out?

790
00:52:52.680 --> 00:52:55.600
Like a special event.
Like a first-class exhibition fight.

791
00:52:57.080 --> 00:52:59.080
- Why me?
- He respects the hell out of you.

792
00:52:59.280 --> 00:53:03.040
All right? And let's be honest,
that computer fight got people curious.

793
00:53:03.240 --> 00:53:05.560
- This could be very interesting.
- I ain't interested...

794
00:53:05.720 --> 00:53:07.760
...in getting, like,
mangled and embarrassed.

795
00:53:07.920 --> 00:53:10.000
No, that's not gonna happen.
Never happen.

796
00:53:10.160 --> 00:53:14.160
Truthfully, I was thinking
more on a, like...

797
00:53:14.560 --> 00:53:18.000
...miniscule, small level.
You know. Small fights, not big fights.

798
00:53:18.280 --> 00:53:22.040
Small fights. Things that...
Local. You know what I mean?

799
00:53:22.200 --> 00:53:25.600
Not a bad idea. Don't think of it as big.
Think of it like an exhibition.

800
00:53:25.760 --> 00:53:29.160
Think of it as a glorified sparring
session. Here's something you'll like.

801
00:53:29.360 --> 00:53:31.760
We're gonna donate a portion
of the gate to charity.

802
00:53:31.920 --> 00:53:33.920
- That's always nice.
- It's good to give.

803
00:53:34.120 --> 00:53:35.520
Yeah.

804
00:53:35.920 --> 00:53:37.440
Where's it taking place?

805
00:53:37.640 --> 00:53:38.920
- Las Vegas.
- Las Vegas.

806
00:53:39.120 --> 00:53:42.200
Nice and warm.
This cold's gotta be killing you.

807
00:53:42.400 --> 00:53:44.680
- Little stiff.
- You move better when you're warmer.

808
00:53:45.240 --> 00:53:46.800
- Yeah.
- And if nothing else...

809
00:53:46.960 --> 00:53:48.960
...you'll have new stories to tell.

810
00:53:49.240 --> 00:53:51.960
- I really gotta think about this.
- Absolutely.

811
00:53:52.120 --> 00:53:54.440
- Is that okay?
- I understand. No problem.

812
00:53:54.800 --> 00:53:56.880
I'm gonna go over there.
You can order something.

813
00:53:57.040 --> 00:53:59.040
- What do you recommend?
- It's all edible.

814
00:54:01.840 --> 00:54:04.360
Okay. Thanks.

815
00:54:04.920 --> 00:54:08.600
We got him. Imagine if Dixon
met this bastard in his prime?

816
00:54:08.760 --> 00:54:11.120
- He'd kill him. Kill him.
- You ain't kidding.

817
00:54:11.640 --> 00:54:13.920
Man, I'm confused.

818
00:54:20.840 --> 00:54:22.640
I didn't think this was gonna
come along.

819
00:54:22.800 --> 00:54:24.360
But this is what you wanted, right?

820
00:54:24.560 --> 00:54:26.760
I don't know.
You know, I talk and I talk.

821
00:54:26.920 --> 00:54:28.920
Sometimes I think
what I'm saying is true...

822
00:54:29.080 --> 00:54:33.240
...and then I look at myself and I'm
not even sure what is true anymore.

823
00:54:33.400 --> 00:54:36.280
Because it's like, I pushed
this crazy idea about fighting.

824
00:54:36.440 --> 00:54:37.920
I mean, what's it all about?

825
00:54:38.120 --> 00:54:40.920
Do I really care about standing
toe to toe and all that stuff...

826
00:54:41.080 --> 00:54:44.520
...or, like my kid says,
is it just, like, ego?

827
00:54:44.720 --> 00:54:48.320
Or am I this old pug who's just trying
to replace old pain with new pain?

828
00:54:48.480 --> 00:54:50.960
I don't know. I don't know.

829
00:54:52.680 --> 00:54:55.320
Look, I know
I usually don't say a lot.

830
00:54:55.480 --> 00:54:59.360
I'm always listening and looking.

831
00:54:59.560 --> 00:55:04.280
But who you are, the part of you
that's so full of life...

832
00:55:04.440 --> 00:55:06.400
...we all have that feeling, that fire...

833
00:55:06.600 --> 00:55:10.880
...but usually never get a chance
to use it. And then it just goes away.

834
00:55:11.080 --> 00:55:15.800
But you can. You've got this
opportunity, so do it. Why not?

835
00:55:15.960 --> 00:55:20.080
I mean, this is who you are.
This is who you'll always be.

836
00:55:20.240 --> 00:55:23.400
And you don't move aside for nobody
until you're ready to move.

837
00:55:23.560 --> 00:55:26.280
And it doesn't matter
how this looks to other people.

838
00:55:26.440 --> 00:55:28.640
All that matters
is how it looks to you.

839
00:55:30.720 --> 00:55:32.160
Rocky.

840
00:55:33.360 --> 00:55:35.240
Rocky, look at me.

841
00:55:36.320 --> 00:55:39.600
How it looks to you.

842
00:55:40.560 --> 00:55:42.480
And if this is something
that you wanna do...

843
00:55:42.640 --> 00:55:46.520
...and if this is something that
you gotta do, then you do it.

844
00:55:47.880 --> 00:55:49.480
Fighters fight.

845
00:55:53.040 --> 00:55:55.400
You're not gonna punch me,
are you?

846
00:55:58.840 --> 00:56:02.320
Listen, I gotta go before I wear out
my welcome. I'll see you tomorrow.

847
00:56:03.720 --> 00:56:05.000
Thanks.

848
00:56:15.400 --> 00:56:17.600
Fighters fight, right?

849
00:56:23.600 --> 00:56:27.360
It's rare when you get to promote
an event bigger than boxing. This is.

850
00:56:27.560 --> 00:56:31.160
Skill versus will, with part
of the proceeds going to charity.

851
00:56:31.320 --> 00:56:35.360
The brainchild of Mason Dixon,
to honor past heavyweight champions.

852
00:56:35.520 --> 00:56:38.600
Warriors like Rocky Balboa.
Let's open it up for questions.

853
00:56:38.800 --> 00:56:39.920
Hey, champ!

854
00:56:40.080 --> 00:56:43.920
A few great fighters have fought in
their 50s, often with disastrous results.

855
00:56:44.080 --> 00:56:45.680
Why risk the danger
and embarrassment?

856
00:56:45.840 --> 00:56:48.200
The smart money says
you have virtually no chance.

857
00:56:48.360 --> 00:56:52.240
A puncher always has a chance.
This fight will be competitive.

858
00:56:53.640 --> 00:56:55.520
Why are you doing this, Rocky?

859
00:56:55.720 --> 00:56:59.720
<i>I don't know, I'd rather do
something I love badly than...</i>

860
00:56:59.880 --> 00:57:04.280
<i>Than to feel bad by not
doing something you love.</i>

861
00:57:05.040 --> 00:57:07.560
Rocky, the press has labeled you
a Balboasaurus.

862
00:57:09.360 --> 00:57:10.960
How do you feel about that?

863
00:57:11.120 --> 00:57:14.920
Let's say the following happens:
You win, we'll say you beat an old guy.

864
00:57:15.080 --> 00:57:18.440
You lose, say a thumb in the eye,
you'll be the joke of the decade.

865
00:57:18.600 --> 00:57:21.880
You all know that will never happen.
This is only an exhibition.

866
00:57:22.040 --> 00:57:25.320
Don't go trying to make more out
of this than that computer tried.

867
00:57:27.120 --> 00:57:30.560
Isn't this sport in enough trouble
without these circus events?

868
00:57:30.880 --> 00:57:33.080
- Next question.
- On the surface, this looks like...

869
00:57:33.240 --> 00:57:35.560
...a cheap bit of ring theater
between, no offense...

870
00:57:35.720 --> 00:57:38.120
...a has-been and a man
whose own credible legacy...

871
00:57:38.320 --> 00:57:39.720
...and popularity is in doubt.

872
00:57:39.880 --> 00:57:41.480
- What's the upside?
- Doubt?

873
00:57:41.640 --> 00:57:44.040
Upside? I mean...

874
00:57:44.240 --> 00:57:47.720
What do you mean, upside?
I mean, what do I have to do?

875
00:57:48.920 --> 00:57:51.080
You know, I'm 33-0
with 30 knockouts.

876
00:57:51.360 --> 00:57:54.160
I'm doing you people a favor.
I'm having this exhibition for you.

877
00:57:54.320 --> 00:57:57.200
You gonna get up here and make
a mockery out of me? I'm the champ.

878
00:57:57.840 --> 00:57:59.920
I mean, I get pissed,
this guy get hurt.

879
00:58:00.840 --> 00:58:02.440
See you at the fight.

880
00:58:06.360 --> 00:58:08.520
The guy's a joke.
He's gonna get crushed.

881
00:58:17.880 --> 00:58:19.560
- Look who's here.
- How you doing?

882
00:58:19.720 --> 00:58:21.880
- Have you seen my father?
- He's in the back.

883
00:58:22.040 --> 00:58:24.760
This place has never served
this many meals. It's unbelievable.

884
00:58:24.920 --> 00:58:28.840
You're doing good? Hope you're
enjoying everything, all right?

885
00:58:31.000 --> 00:58:32.480
Excuse me.

886
00:58:34.080 --> 00:58:37.480
How you doing? Glad you come by.

887
00:58:38.040 --> 00:58:39.120
Can I talk with you?

888
00:58:39.400 --> 00:58:41.800
- Sure.
- Can we do it outside?

889
00:58:46.480 --> 00:58:49.160
- So you're going through with this?
- I start training tomorrow.

890
00:58:49.360 --> 00:58:52.440
Hey, Rock.
I made some connections.

891
00:58:52.600 --> 00:58:54.880
I can make some money
on this, endorsements.

892
00:58:56.000 --> 00:58:57.160
Absolutely. Do that.

893
00:58:57.520 --> 00:58:59.880
- Thank you, Rock. Okay.
- Sure.

894
00:59:00.520 --> 00:59:03.800
- So you nervous about the fight?
- Scared to death.

895
00:59:03.960 --> 00:59:06.600
- You don't look scared.
- Well, I ain't supposed to.

896
00:59:06.760 --> 00:59:09.040
Then you don't have to do it.

897
00:59:09.200 --> 00:59:11.400
Yeah, well, I think I do.

898
00:59:14.400 --> 00:59:17.440
You know, living with you,
it hasn't been easy.

899
00:59:17.600 --> 00:59:20.120
People see me
but they think of you.

900
00:59:20.280 --> 00:59:23.000
Now with all this going on,
it's gonna be worse than ever.

901
00:59:23.160 --> 00:59:25.000
- It don't have to be.
- Sure it does!

902
00:59:25.200 --> 00:59:27.800
- Why? You've got a lot going on, kid.
- What, my last name?

903
00:59:27.960 --> 00:59:29.800
That's the reason I got a decent job.

904
00:59:30.000 --> 00:59:32.080
That's why people deal with me
in the first place.

905
00:59:32.240 --> 00:59:33.840
Now I start to get a little ahead...

906
00:59:34.000 --> 00:59:37.800
...I start to get a little something
for myself, and this happens.

907
00:59:37.960 --> 00:59:41.080
Now, I'm asking you as a favor
not to go through with this.

908
00:59:41.240 --> 00:59:44.280
This is gonna end up bad for you,
and it's gonna end up bad for me.

909
00:59:44.440 --> 00:59:47.080
- You think I'm hurting you?
- Yeah. In a way, you are.

910
00:59:47.400 --> 00:59:49.160
That's the last thing
I ever wanted to do.

911
00:59:49.320 --> 00:59:52.640
I know that's not what you wanna do,
but that's just the way that it is.

912
00:59:52.800 --> 00:59:55.760
Don't you care what people think?
Doesn't it bother you that people...

913
00:59:55.920 --> 00:59:58.880
...are making you out to be a joke
and that I'll be included in that?

914
00:59:59.040 --> 01:00:01.920
Do you think that's right? Do you?

915
01:00:07.720 --> 01:00:12.440
You ain't gonna believe this,
but you used to fit right here.

916
01:00:12.600 --> 01:00:14.760
I'd hold you up
and say to your mother:

917
01:00:14.920 --> 01:00:17.360
"This kid is gonna be
the best kid in the world.

918
01:00:17.520 --> 01:00:20.640
This kid is gonna be somebody
better than anybody ever knew."

919
01:00:20.800 --> 01:00:23.520
And you grew up
good and wonderful.

920
01:00:23.680 --> 01:00:26.680
It was great just watching,
every day was like a privilege.

921
01:00:26.840 --> 01:00:29.920
Then the time come for you to be
your own man and take on the world...

922
01:00:30.080 --> 01:00:34.400
...and you did. But somewhere
along the line, you changed.

923
01:00:34.600 --> 01:00:35.800
You stopped being you.

924
01:00:35.960 --> 01:00:39.120
You let people stick a finger in
your face and tell you you're no good.

925
01:00:39.280 --> 01:00:42.800
And when things got hard, you started
looking for something to blame...

926
01:00:42.960 --> 01:00:44.960
...like a big shadow.

927
01:00:46.400 --> 01:00:48.560
Let me tell you something
you already know.

928
01:00:48.720 --> 01:00:50.960
The world ain't all
sunshine and rainbows.

929
01:00:51.120 --> 01:00:54.800
It's a very mean and nasty place,
and I don't care how tough you are...

930
01:00:54.960 --> 01:00:58.400
...it will beat you to your knees
and keep you there if you let it.

931
01:00:59.040 --> 01:01:02.880
You, me or nobody
is gonna hit as hard as life.

932
01:01:03.040 --> 01:01:07.000
But it ain't about how hard you hit.
It's about how hard you can get hit...

933
01:01:07.160 --> 01:01:08.520
...and keep moving forward.

934
01:01:08.680 --> 01:01:11.720
How much you can take
and keep moving forward.

935
01:01:11.880 --> 01:01:14.200
That's how winning is done!

936
01:01:14.640 --> 01:01:17.280
If you know what you're worth,
go and get what you're worth.

937
01:01:17.440 --> 01:01:20.560
But you gotta be willing to take
the hits, and not pointing fingers...

938
01:01:20.720 --> 01:01:24.680
...saying you ain't where you wanna be
because of him or her or anybody!

939
01:01:24.840 --> 01:01:28.880
Cowards do that, and that ain't you!
You're better than that!

940
01:01:35.360 --> 01:01:38.560
I'm always gonna love you
no matter what.

941
01:01:38.720 --> 01:01:40.520
No matter what happens.

942
01:01:40.840 --> 01:01:43.560
You're my son and you're my blood.

943
01:01:43.720 --> 01:01:46.360
You're the best thing in my life.

944
01:01:47.560 --> 01:01:51.240
But until you start believing in
yourself, you ain't gonna have a life.

945
01:01:55.920 --> 01:01:58.280
Don't forget to visit your mother.

946
01:02:46.120 --> 01:02:48.640
- Yeah, those are beautiful.
- Yeah.

947
01:02:50.520 --> 01:02:53.480
- You get off early from work?
- No.

948
01:02:53.920 --> 01:02:55.360
I left.

949
01:02:55.960 --> 01:02:57.440
I quit.

950
01:02:58.160 --> 01:02:59.400
Quit, why?

951
01:03:00.760 --> 01:03:03.040
I wasn't very...

952
01:03:03.640 --> 01:03:06.640
I don't know, I just...
I didn't fit in there.

953
01:03:08.600 --> 01:03:09.960
I understand.

954
01:03:14.440 --> 01:03:17.600
- So, what are you gonna do?
- Right now?

955
01:03:19.040 --> 01:03:21.520
Right now I'd rather be with you.

956
01:03:23.760 --> 01:03:25.480
Is that all right?

957
01:03:26.760 --> 01:03:28.520
Yeah.

958
01:03:28.840 --> 01:03:31.560
It's been a long time
since I seen a fight.

959
01:03:42.920 --> 01:03:42.960
You know all there is
to know about fighting...

960
01:03:42.960 --> 01:03:45.040
You know all there is
to know about fighting...

961
01:03:45.200 --> 01:03:48.240
...so there's no sense us going down
that same old road again.

962
01:03:48.400 --> 01:03:52.360
To beat this guy, you need speed.
You don't have it.

963
01:03:53.800 --> 01:03:57.600
And your knees can't take the
pounding, so hard running is out.

964
01:03:57.760 --> 01:04:01.320
And you got arthritis in your neck.
And you've got calcium deposits...

965
01:04:01.480 --> 01:04:04.680
...on most of your joints,
so sparring is out.

966
01:04:05.560 --> 01:04:06.960
I had that problem.

967
01:04:07.840 --> 01:04:12.840
So what we'll be calling on is good
old-fashioned blunt-force trauma.

968
01:04:13.000 --> 01:04:17.480
Horsepower. Heavy-duty,
cast-iron, pile-driving punches...

969
01:04:17.640 --> 01:04:20.520
...that will have to hurt so much
they'll rattle his ancestors.

970
01:04:21.080 --> 01:04:22.760
Every time you hit him with a shot...

971
01:04:22.920 --> 01:04:25.760
...it's gotta feel like he tried kissing
the express train.

972
01:04:27.040 --> 01:04:30.800
Yeah! Let's start building
some hurting bombs.

973
01:05:01.800 --> 01:05:04.520
- Yeah, you'll get it.
- You can do it, Rocko!

974
01:05:38.920 --> 01:05:40.400
Getting stronger!

975
01:05:42.720 --> 01:05:44.360
- Up! Up! Up!
- Come on!

976
01:05:46.240 --> 01:05:47.440
Go!

977
01:05:52.360 --> 01:05:55.080
- Yeah!
- Yeah! Yeah!

978
01:05:57.680 --> 01:05:59.040
Come on, Rocko!

979
01:06:06.120 --> 01:06:08.360
Come on. Come on.
Let's hit them. Hit them.

980
01:06:13.640 --> 01:06:14.920
You can do it, Rock.

981
01:06:17.920 --> 01:06:19.080
Getting stronger!

982
01:06:29.640 --> 01:06:32.400
- Up, up, up!
- Go! Go!

983
01:06:33.520 --> 01:06:34.920
All right!

984
01:06:35.440 --> 01:06:36.680
Yeah! Yeah!

985
01:06:55.560 --> 01:06:57.120
Yeah!

986
01:07:06.520 --> 01:07:10.400
Rocky Balboa, 217!

987
01:07:11.120 --> 01:07:17.000
The undisputed heavyweight
champion, Mason Dixon, 221!

988
01:07:19.880 --> 01:07:22.760
Thank you very much.
I appreciate it, champ. Thanks a lot.

989
01:07:28.640 --> 01:07:33.120
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

990
01:07:38.440 --> 01:07:40.440
- Know how much money is in this?
- A lot of it.

991
01:07:40.600 --> 01:07:42.880
Imagine trying to clean this place.

992
01:07:43.040 --> 01:07:44.360
- No, seriously.
- Balboa!

993
01:07:47.880 --> 01:07:50.560
You guys, I'll catch up
with you all later, okay?

994
01:07:50.720 --> 01:07:52.840
Robert, why don't
you hang with me?

995
01:07:53.960 --> 01:07:56.760
- How you doing, champ?
- I'm good.

996
01:07:58.200 --> 01:08:00.720
No reason for neither one of us
to get hurt in this fight.

997
01:08:00.880 --> 01:08:03.760
I'll do my best to carry you,
make sure you save face.

998
01:08:03.920 --> 01:08:05.640
There'd be no embarrassment.

999
01:08:05.800 --> 01:08:09.960
But I promise you, you try to press me,
you hit me, you hurt me...

1000
01:08:10.120 --> 01:08:13.520
...you hit me low, cheap-shot me,
I'll get you out of there.

1001
01:08:14.920 --> 01:08:18.920
You know, a lot of people come
to Vegas to lose. I didn't.

1002
01:08:19.080 --> 01:08:20.360
It's already over.

1003
01:08:20.520 --> 01:08:22.320
Ain't nothing over till it's over.

1004
01:08:22.480 --> 01:08:24.080
What's that from, the '80s?

1005
01:08:24.240 --> 01:08:26.520
That's probably the '70s.

1006
01:08:29.280 --> 01:08:30.720
Just remember what I said.

1007
01:08:32.200 --> 01:08:34.120
Hey, yo, champ.

1008
01:08:34.360 --> 01:08:35.920
Yo, ain't you a little scared?

1009
01:08:36.840 --> 01:08:38.600
I don't get scared.

1010
01:08:41.560 --> 01:08:43.880
I think you try a little harder
when you're scared.

1011
01:08:44.480 --> 01:08:47.560
This is what has worked for me.

1012
01:08:48.240 --> 01:08:50.520
- I ain't scared.
- Oh, yeah. You ain't scared of me?

1013
01:08:50.680 --> 01:08:53.000
Come on, let's see what you got.
Come on.

1014
01:08:53.160 --> 01:08:54.520
Hey, don't hit me, I'm brittle.

1015
01:09:09.560 --> 01:09:11.200
- Hey.
- Hi.

1016
01:09:11.360 --> 01:09:12.960
- How you doing?
- I was just thinking.

1017
01:09:13.120 --> 01:09:15.320
- Did you wanna come in?
- No, no, no, it's okay.

1018
01:09:15.480 --> 01:09:17.560
I just wanted to...

1019
01:09:17.720 --> 01:09:20.400
...I don' t know, come by and wish you
good luck for tomorrow.

1020
01:09:20.560 --> 01:09:22.320
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

1021
01:09:22.480 --> 01:09:24.360
I brought you something.

1022
01:09:24.520 --> 01:09:26.760
I hope you don't mind,
I took it from the restaurant.

1023
01:09:26.920 --> 01:09:28.680
- No.
- Thanks.

1024
01:09:28.840 --> 01:09:30.520
Adrian.

1025
01:09:30.680 --> 01:09:33.320
Yeah. Thought she would
keep you safe.

1026
01:09:33.480 --> 01:09:35.840
Yeah. Yeah, she always
brought me luck.

1027
01:09:36.000 --> 01:09:37.640
Yeah.

1028
01:09:38.320 --> 01:09:43.200
I wanted to say thanks for everything
you've done for me and my kid.

1029
01:09:43.920 --> 01:09:45.800
You've been great and...

1030
01:09:50.000 --> 01:09:51.840
You know, tomorrow...

1031
01:09:53.240 --> 01:09:57.080
...you're gonna prove that the last thing
to age on somebody is their heart.

1032
01:09:59.040 --> 01:10:01.160
- I'll try.
- You go show them.

1033
01:10:01.320 --> 01:10:02.920
Thank you.

1034
01:10:23.240 --> 01:10:25.000
<i>The heavyweight championship
has been...</i>

1035
01:10:25.160 --> 01:10:28.560
<i>... one of sports' most coveted titles
for 120 years.</i>

1036
01:10:28.880 --> 01:10:31.200
<i>Two-time heavyweight champion
Rocky Balboa...</i>

1037
01:10:31.360 --> 01:10:34.320
<i>... the Philadelphia slugger,
renowned for his cast-iron jaw...</i>

1038
01:10:34.480 --> 01:10:37.160
<i>... ferocious body attack
and will of steel...</i>

1039
01:10:37.640 --> 01:10:40.360
<i>... all of which have carried
the smaller fighter to victories...</i>

1040
01:10:40.520 --> 01:10:43.800
<i>... over the years against
physically superior opponents.</i>

1041
01:10:43.960 --> 01:10:46.440
<i>And Mason Dixon, the current
heavyweight title holder...</i>

1042
01:10:46.600 --> 01:10:49.840
<i>... with all the speed, determination
and confidence any fighter could want.</i>

1043
01:10:50.000 --> 01:10:53.800
<i>But many still question whether
he has the heart of a true champion...</i>

1044
01:10:53.960 --> 01:10:57.640
<i>... never having been pushed to go
the distance. Tonight, we find out.</i>

1045
01:10:59.160 --> 01:11:01.520
<i>Here at the Mandalay Bay
Event Center in Las Vegas...</i>

1046
01:11:01.680 --> 01:11:03.440
<i>... for the much-anticipated
showdown...</i>

1047
01:11:03.600 --> 01:11:05.480
<i>... between Mason
"The Line" Dixon...</i>

1048
01:11:05.640 --> 01:11:08.400
<i>... and Rocky
"The Italian Stallion" Balboa.</i>

1049
01:11:08.880 --> 01:11:11.720
Hello, I'm Jim Lampley with
Larry Merchant and Max Kellerman...

1050
01:11:11.880 --> 01:11:14.920
...live from the Mandalay Bay Hotel
in Las Vegas, where we anticipate...

1051
01:11:15.080 --> 01:11:18.160
...one of the most outrageous and
compelling events in boxing history.

1052
01:11:18.320 --> 01:11:21.920
The unappreciated heavyweight
champion, Mason "The Line" Dixon...

1053
01:11:22.080 --> 01:11:23.760
<i>... putting his reputation
on the line...</i>

1054
01:11:25.040 --> 01:11:26.760
<i>... against legendary ex-champion,
Rocky Balboa.</i>

1055
01:11:28.040 --> 01:11:31.000
<i>Even though most see this as more
of a glorified sparring session...</i>

1056
01:11:31.160 --> 01:11:33.040
...the energy in the room is electric.

1057
01:11:33.200 --> 01:11:35.200
Larry, why is this billed
as an exhibition?

1058
01:11:35.400 --> 01:11:39.400
Wild guess: So they wouldn't
have to call it an execution.

1059
01:11:40.160 --> 01:11:45.160
Zacariah 4:6 says,
"It is not by strength, not by might...

1060
01:11:45.320 --> 01:11:48.920
...but by his spirit
we have already claimed the victory...

1061
01:11:49.080 --> 01:11:51.680
...in our Lord Jesus Christ."

1062
01:11:52.280 --> 01:11:53.920
Good luck, Rocky.

1063
01:11:54.080 --> 01:11:56.240
Thanks, Spider. Appreciate it.

1064
01:12:06.920 --> 01:12:10.040
Nobody's expecting much, I think,
from the way-past-his-prime...

1065
01:12:10.200 --> 01:12:12.200
...former champ, Rocky Balboa.

1066
01:12:12.680 --> 01:12:15.800
Rock, I gotta talk to you.

1067
01:12:16.520 --> 01:12:22.120
Look, I know you got a lot of stuff
you gotta get out of your system.

1068
01:12:23.000 --> 01:12:27.360
Tonight you do it. Right?
Get rid of the damn beast...

1069
01:12:27.560 --> 01:12:32.200
...let it be done, once and for all.
Please, I love you.

1070
01:12:33.040 --> 01:12:36.520
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1071
01:12:41.160 --> 01:12:45.360
There go the lights. The buzz is
building toward a roaring crescendo.

1072
01:13:00.640 --> 01:13:02.720
Where did that come from?

1073
01:13:02.920 --> 01:13:05.760
I told you. I love Sinatra.

1074
01:13:06.440 --> 01:13:08.360
He's very good, Sinatra.

1075
01:13:08.520 --> 01:13:11.440
- Let's go.
- Very good.

1076
01:13:13.600 --> 01:13:17.920
And here comes Rocky Balboa,
veteran of the wars...

1077
01:13:18.120 --> 01:13:20.680
...here for one more last hurrah.

1078
01:13:20.840 --> 01:13:23.640
Or the Last Supper, perhaps,
with him as the main course.

1079
01:13:23.800 --> 01:13:26.320
What's that music?
You can't be serious.

1080
01:13:26.480 --> 01:13:29.120
"High Hopes"?
Talk about wishful thinking.

1081
01:13:29.320 --> 01:13:32.640
Well, maybe no hopes is more
realistic. Anyway, the crowd likes it.

1082
01:13:33.440 --> 01:13:36.520
Look at the Italian Stallion.
Cool and relaxed.

1083
01:13:36.680 --> 01:13:40.240
Rocky's an off-the-board underdog,
and they don't care at all.

1084
01:13:40.400 --> 01:13:44.040
This is about his pride and dignity
and his punch, guys.

1085
01:13:44.240 --> 01:13:46.680
The last thing to go
is a guy's punch.

1086
01:13:46.840 --> 01:13:50.160
Rocky always has
that puncher's chance.

1087
01:13:54.320 --> 01:13:58.240
Rocky Balboa is still, as you can hear,
the people's champion.

1088
01:13:58.440 --> 01:14:00.760
Prediction, guys:
For at least two rounds...

1089
01:14:00.920 --> 01:14:02.600
...Dixon's gonna have
his hands full.

1090
01:14:02.760 --> 01:14:06.600
Two whole rounds? We have
a cockeyed optimist in the house.

1091
01:14:07.560 --> 01:14:09.320
- How you doing?
- The crowd wants to see...

1092
01:14:09.480 --> 01:14:11.040
...something real, or at least...

1093
01:14:11.240 --> 01:14:13.160
Rocky Balboa just asked me
how I'm doing.

1094
01:14:13.320 --> 01:14:17.800
I grew up watching this guy. I never
thought I'd be calling one of his fights.

1095
01:14:18.280 --> 01:14:20.880
This is unbelievable.
I'm a fan, I can't help it.

1096
01:14:21.040 --> 01:14:23.560
Now here comes Mason Dixon.

1097
01:14:56.400 --> 01:14:58.760
Mason Dixon establishing
his presence in the ring.

1098
01:14:58.920 --> 01:15:02.560
And suddenly now a conversation
breaking out at ringside.

1099
01:15:02.720 --> 01:15:05.320
Mike Tyson calling out
Mason "The Line" Dixon.

1100
01:15:05.480 --> 01:15:07.920
You can't call no shots here.
I'm the champ.

1101
01:15:08.080 --> 01:15:10.360
You not doing nothing.
This is charity work.

1102
01:15:10.520 --> 01:15:13.440
You got that midget
with you right there.

1103
01:15:17.960 --> 01:15:21.320
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the Mandalay Bay...

1104
01:15:22.880 --> 01:15:25.280
...resort and casino of Las Vegas.

1105
01:15:25.480 --> 01:15:28.800
And a special main event
of the evening...

1106
01:15:28.960 --> 01:15:32.120
...10 rounds of
heavyweight excitement...

1107
01:15:32.280 --> 01:15:34.600
...sanctioned by the Nevada
State Athletic Commission.

1108
01:15:34.760 --> 01:15:38.480
And when the bell rings, the referee
in charge of the action, Joe Cortez.

1109
01:15:40.200 --> 01:15:43.200
And now, for the thousands
in attendance...

1110
01:15:43.360 --> 01:15:48.840
...and the millions watching around
the world, ladies and gentlemen...

1111
01:15:49.000 --> 01:15:54.360
...let's get ready to rumble!

1112
01:15:56.680 --> 01:15:59.720
Introducing first,
fighting out of the blue corner...

1113
01:15:59.880 --> 01:16:04.360
...wearing black with gold,
official weight, 217 pounds.

1114
01:16:04.520 --> 01:16:08.960
His professional record, 57 victories
including 54 knockouts...

1115
01:16:09.160 --> 01:16:12.040
...with 23 defeats and one draw.

1116
01:16:12.200 --> 01:16:15.240
He is the fighting pride
of Philadelphia...

1117
01:16:15.520 --> 01:16:19.720
...the two-time heavyweight
champion of the world...

1118
01:16:19.880 --> 01:16:21.880
..."The Italian Stallion"...

1119
01:16:22.040 --> 01:16:26.440
...Rocky...

1120
01:16:26.600 --> 01:16:28.880
...Balboa!

1121
01:16:31.800 --> 01:16:33.320
Hope he gets his head busted.

1122
01:16:35.280 --> 01:16:37.160
Shut up.

1123
01:16:39.800 --> 01:16:42.480
Across the ring,
fighting out of the red corner...

1124
01:16:42.640 --> 01:16:46.280
...wearing white with blue,
official weight, 221 pounds.

1125
01:16:46.520 --> 01:16:51.320
He has a perfect professional record,
consisting of 33 bouts...

1126
01:16:51.480 --> 01:16:54.600
...33 victories,
including 30 knockouts.

1127
01:16:54.760 --> 01:16:56.680
Originally from Tampa, Florida...

1128
01:16:56.840 --> 01:16:59.720
...but now fighting out
of Las Vegas, Nevada...

1129
01:16:59.880 --> 01:17:04.040
...the reigning undisputed,
undefeated...

1130
01:17:04.200 --> 01:17:07.080
...heavyweight champion
of the world...

1131
01:17:07.240 --> 01:17:10.560
...Mason "The Line"...

1132
01:17:10.760 --> 01:17:14.560
...Dixon!

1133
01:17:18.520 --> 01:17:20.120
All right, gentlemen.

1134
01:17:20.280 --> 01:17:23.520
All right, Mason, Rocky. We went
over the rules in the dressing room.

1135
01:17:23.680 --> 01:17:27.520
I expect a good, clean fight. Watch
the kidney punches, rabbit punches...

1136
01:17:27.720 --> 01:17:30.760
...low blows, be careful with those.
Give me good sportsmanlike conduct.

1137
01:17:30.920 --> 01:17:34.480
Remember, gentlemen, I'm fair
but I'm firm. Touch them up!

1138
01:17:34.640 --> 01:17:37.120
- Enjoy the ride.
- The champ is not in the best shape...

1139
01:17:37.280 --> 01:17:40.440
...we've seen him in. Maybe he plans
to phone this in and go home early.

1140
01:17:40.600 --> 01:17:42.920
- That wouldn't be a surprise.
- Glad you could make it.

1141
01:17:43.080 --> 01:17:45.600
One thing about Rocky
we know for sure:

1142
01:17:45.800 --> 01:17:47.920
This guy's showing up in shape.

1143
01:17:48.080 --> 01:17:50.800
- The old man's crazy.
- He's gotta be crazy. He's in here.

1144
01:17:50.960 --> 01:17:52.840
- Okay.
- Take it easy. This is an exhibition.

1145
01:17:53.000 --> 01:17:54.400
All right? Do it to him.

1146
01:17:54.560 --> 01:17:57.640
You got three rounds to set a pace.
Every time you hit him, make a dent.

1147
01:17:57.800 --> 01:17:59.680
- Got it.
- The moments before...

1148
01:17:59.840 --> 01:18:03.200
...a Rocky Balboa fight?
I can't believe it's here!

1149
01:18:04.280 --> 01:18:05.480
Round one begins.

1150
01:18:05.640 --> 01:18:09.160
If old George Foreman shocked
the world with one punch...

1151
01:18:09.320 --> 01:18:11.360
...why can't old Rocky Balboa?

1152
01:18:11.560 --> 01:18:13.800
And as much excitement
as there is in the arena...

1153
01:18:13.960 --> 01:18:16.200
...there's a sense of foreboding
as well.

1154
01:18:20.360 --> 01:18:23.880
And now, Mason "The Line" Dixon
goes to work with his jab as though...

1155
01:18:24.040 --> 01:18:27.760
...he's fighting against the number one
challenger in the heavyweight division.

1156
01:18:28.200 --> 01:18:30.000
See, this is to be expected early on.

1157
01:18:30.160 --> 01:18:32.760
You knew the champ would
control the distance with his jab...

1158
01:18:32.920 --> 01:18:34.880
...his height, his range.

1159
01:18:36.200 --> 01:18:39.160
Balboa looking to get in a shot,
misses wildly.

1160
01:18:39.320 --> 01:18:41.080
Did you like that?

1161
01:18:41.520 --> 01:18:44.520
It looks like a speed bag
against a punching bag.

1162
01:18:44.720 --> 01:18:46.240
Rocky's understandably frustrated...

1163
01:18:46.440 --> 01:18:48.680
...but he came out of retirement
to get into a fight.

1164
01:18:48.840 --> 01:18:51.280
Guys named Rocky
don't like to be toyed with.

1165
01:18:51.440 --> 01:18:53.080
One punch could still turn it around.

1166
01:18:53.280 --> 01:18:56.240
Apparently he forgot
his arthritis meds this morning.

1167
01:18:56.520 --> 01:18:57.960
Rocky misses.

1168
01:18:58.280 --> 01:19:01.880
There's a meat-seeking missile
on the point of the chin by the champ.

1169
01:19:02.040 --> 01:19:04.680
<i>- More pinpoint jabs by Dixon.
- Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1170
01:19:04.840 --> 01:19:08.040
And there's a hard right hand
and a left and a right by Balboa!

1171
01:19:08.200 --> 01:19:11.040
He drives Dixon into the ropes
with a series of shots!

1172
01:19:11.200 --> 01:19:13.520
And the crowd goes berserk!

1173
01:19:18.160 --> 01:19:22.280
Dixon punishing Balboa for
the temerity of landing those shots.

1174
01:19:25.640 --> 01:19:30.040
It's toe to toe in the corner.
Balboa and Dixon letting it all go.

1175
01:19:36.520 --> 01:19:39.240
Balboa landing potent combinations
to the head of the champion.

1176
01:19:39.560 --> 01:19:40.760
A wake-up call for Dixon.

1177
01:19:40.920 --> 01:19:42.480
- You all right?
- Yeah, I'm all right.

1178
01:19:42.640 --> 01:19:45.720
- The man's got bricks in his gloves.
- Where's the stuff in the basement?

1179
01:19:45.880 --> 01:19:48.000
- It's still there.
- He came to battle, okay?

1180
01:19:48.160 --> 01:19:49.560
- Trying to knock me out.
- Listen.

1181
01:19:49.720 --> 01:19:52.040
If there's a bone he can break,
he's gonna do it.

1182
01:19:52.200 --> 01:19:54.440
- Give the man respect.
- What about my respect?

1183
01:19:54.600 --> 01:19:57.320
CompuBox numbers
tell the grisly story here.

1184
01:19:57.480 --> 01:20:00.400
Balboa landed nine of 13
punches in that round.

1185
01:20:00.560 --> 01:20:05.520
Dixon landed an incredible
59 out of 69.

1186
01:20:05.680 --> 01:20:09.000
- Why don't you listen to me?
- Rocky's been here a million times.

1187
01:20:09.160 --> 01:20:12.240
Coming out to start a round after
he took a beating in the previous one.

1188
01:20:12.400 --> 01:20:15.440
- Remember what I said, okay?
- I warned him. I warned him.

1189
01:20:16.480 --> 01:20:21.200
He's tired. His legs are going fast,
or already gone.

1190
01:20:21.360 --> 01:20:25.760
And what's truly extraordinary
is that Rocky can still take it.

1191
01:20:25.920 --> 01:20:30.640
The boxing commission, which
was criticized for licensing him...

1192
01:20:30.800 --> 01:20:34.880
...would be massacred
if something happened to Rocky.

1193
01:20:38.040 --> 01:20:40.600
And a monstrous straight left hand!
Down goes Rocky!

1194
01:20:40.800 --> 01:20:43.000
And that could conceivably
be the end of the fight!

1195
01:20:43.160 --> 01:20:46.840
That could be the exhibition
right there. But no. Balboa up.

1196
01:20:47.000 --> 01:20:51.120
Referee Joe Cortez asks if he wants
to continue, and Rocky says yes.

1197
01:20:51.280 --> 01:20:54.040
Even Rocky Balboa could be
too brave for his own good.

1198
01:20:54.200 --> 01:20:57.640
Dixon comes right back to try to
finish it. Balboa almost went down!

1199
01:20:57.800 --> 01:20:59.720
Rocky actually shoves Dixon back.

1200
01:20:59.880 --> 01:21:02.320
As Dixon lands these brutal shots.

1201
01:21:02.480 --> 01:21:04.960
- Cover up! Cover up!
- Open shots at close range.

1202
01:21:05.120 --> 01:21:07.520
Right and left hands,
and down goes Balboa!

1203
01:21:07.720 --> 01:21:10.920
Perhaps for the last time
in his fighting career!

1204
01:21:11.080 --> 01:21:13.400
- That should do it.
- Three! Four!

1205
01:21:13.560 --> 01:21:15.800
Five! Six!

1206
01:21:15.960 --> 01:21:17.520
Get up! Get up!
- Seven!

1207
01:21:17.680 --> 01:21:19.400
Eight! Nine!

1208
01:21:20.800 --> 01:21:23.880
- How do you feel, man? You okay?
- Now Rocky is furious with himself.

1209
01:21:24.040 --> 01:21:26.520
He convinces Cortez
he wants to keep fighting.

1210
01:21:26.680 --> 01:21:28.480
Dixon's pointing at the ref to end it.

1211
01:21:28.640 --> 01:21:30.640
Rocky waving his arms
and saying he's fine.

1212
01:21:30.800 --> 01:21:32.880
- He wants to go on!
- Let it go! Let it go!

1213
01:21:33.800 --> 01:21:36.720
And Balboa comes back!
With a left and a right...

1214
01:21:36.880 --> 01:21:40.640
...and bulls Dixon into the ropes
for the second round in a row!

1215
01:21:41.800 --> 01:21:44.240
Back comes Dixon
with brutal left-hand shots.

1216
01:21:44.400 --> 01:21:46.520
- Dixon hurt his hand there!
- Go after him!

1217
01:21:46.680 --> 01:21:48.280
This is Rocky's best chance!

1218
01:21:48.440 --> 01:21:50.600
The champ obviously hurt
his hand on Rocky's hip!

1219
01:21:50.760 --> 01:21:54.440
And Balboa immediately going to
work to the body! Huge right hook!

1220
01:21:54.600 --> 01:21:58.000
Balboa ripping away at Dixon's body!
These are big punches.

1221
01:21:58.240 --> 01:22:01.800
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1222
01:22:03.160 --> 01:22:04.160
Yes!

1223
01:22:06.520 --> 01:22:10.800
Rocky Balboa has knocked the
reigning heavyweight champion down!

1224
01:22:10.960 --> 01:22:12.800
- You hurt him!
- Mason "The Line" Dixon...

1225
01:22:12.960 --> 01:22:14.920
...has never taken
this kind of punishment...

1226
01:22:15.080 --> 01:22:17.160
...in his entire professional career!

1227
01:22:17.320 --> 01:22:21.160
Maybe he's clearing his head, but
the body shots really caved in his ribs.

1228
01:22:21.320 --> 01:22:23.880
Balboa is thinking knockout himself!

1229
01:22:24.040 --> 01:22:27.440
Another counterhook by Balboa,
followed by two more!

1230
01:22:27.600 --> 01:22:30.000
Dixon fires back his own hooks!
Now Rocky's stunned.

1231
01:22:30.160 --> 01:22:32.600
It's an all-out war along the ropes...

1232
01:22:32.760 --> 01:22:37.600
...as round two comes to a close
amid a giant tumult in the ring!

1233
01:22:38.280 --> 01:22:39.800
Incredible.

1234
01:22:39.960 --> 01:22:41.560
All right!

1235
01:22:41.720 --> 01:22:43.440
Welcome to Rockyland.

1236
01:22:47.400 --> 01:22:49.720
- How's the hand?
- My hand's broken.

1237
01:22:51.720 --> 01:22:53.680
We lose, it's your ass! Your ass!

1238
01:22:53.840 --> 01:22:56.040
It will numb up on you
in a few rounds.

1239
01:22:56.200 --> 01:22:59.680
Once that hand numbs up,
Dixon will be able to throw it hard.

1240
01:22:59.840 --> 01:23:02.120
Until then, here is Rocky's chance.

1241
01:23:02.280 --> 01:23:04.920
- No reverse!
- Take the pain, champ.

1242
01:23:05.080 --> 01:23:07.760
Stay on him! Everybody thought
this was a joke, including me!

1243
01:23:07.920 --> 01:23:10.440
Now nobody's laughing!
Stay on him! You go get him!

1244
01:23:11.200 --> 01:23:13.000
Go out strong!

1245
01:23:24.360 --> 01:23:25.280
Keep him off you!

1246
01:23:29.000 --> 01:23:29.960
That's it! That's it!

1247
01:23:43.840 --> 01:23:45.800
You won that round.
Break him down.

1248
01:23:51.240 --> 01:23:53.160
Bomb him! Bomb him!

1249
01:23:58.640 --> 01:23:59.800
Yeah!

1250
01:24:03.560 --> 01:24:05.800
Just keep throwing them bombs!

1251
01:24:17.080 --> 01:24:18.200
Come on.

1252
01:24:25.440 --> 01:24:27.400
You can do this.

1253
01:24:28.240 --> 01:24:30.920
Rocko. Rocko.

1254
01:24:39.160 --> 01:24:41.440
Yeah, come on, go!

1255
01:25:36.160 --> 01:25:37.960
Go through him! Run over him!

1256
01:25:52.760 --> 01:25:53.960
Unload on him!

1257
01:25:55.720 --> 01:25:56.680
Get down, Mason!

1258
01:26:08.040 --> 01:26:09.920
They're leaving nothing
on the table, guys.

1259
01:26:10.120 --> 01:26:14.440
The fans are still standing. They may
not be able to sit down for a week.

1260
01:26:14.600 --> 01:26:17.280
- You're doing great!
- I'm doing better than I thought.

1261
01:26:17.440 --> 01:26:21.080
- You sure he's okay?
- I've had worse.

1262
01:26:21.240 --> 01:26:24.840
Toe to toe, one round to go. Who
would've believed this was possible?

1263
01:26:25.000 --> 01:26:27.240
- Can you see out of that eye?
- Let me talk to him.

1264
01:26:27.640 --> 01:26:29.600
Don't take any more chances
than you have to.

1265
01:26:29.760 --> 01:26:32.600
There's nothing more to prove, Pop.
There's nothing more to prove.

1266
01:26:32.760 --> 01:26:34.800
I gotta go out the way I gotta go out.

1267
01:26:34.960 --> 01:26:36.480
You can do it, Rocko!

1268
01:26:36.680 --> 01:26:38.880
- One more round, we go home.
- Okay, then do it.

1269
01:26:39.040 --> 01:26:42.400
There's an old saying that
every great champion has...

1270
01:26:42.600 --> 01:26:47.680
...one great fight left in him,
and Rocky is proving it so far.

1271
01:26:47.840 --> 01:26:50.920
- Come on. Touch them up.
- Rocko! The last round of your life!

1272
01:26:51.080 --> 01:26:52.640
- Come on, guys.
- The last round!

1273
01:26:52.840 --> 01:26:55.080
Come on. Touch them up, let's go.
Touch them up.

1274
01:26:55.720 --> 01:26:58.520
- You are one crazy old man.
- You'll get there.

1275
01:26:58.960 --> 01:27:00.080
Let's go.

1276
01:27:00.360 --> 01:27:03.480
Tenth round of a scheduled 10.
Who would ever have dreamed...

1277
01:27:03.640 --> 01:27:08.240
...that Rocky Balboa would still be
in this quote, "exhibition," against...

1278
01:27:08.400 --> 01:27:11.080
...the heavyweight champion?
- You can do it! Come on!

1279
01:27:11.240 --> 01:27:15.400
This fight is as though Dixon
got on-the-job training in courage.

1280
01:27:16.440 --> 01:27:19.080
- Cover up! Cover up!
- They're both in a pain-free zone!

1281
01:27:19.240 --> 01:27:22.360
These guys are fighting
in another dimension right now!

1282
01:27:22.520 --> 01:27:26.400
Beyond belief! Balboa just walking
straight into Dixon's punches.

1283
01:27:26.600 --> 01:27:29.080
Target practice for Dixon.

1284
01:27:32.360 --> 01:27:34.760
They're exchanging right hooks!
Balboa's drilled!

1285
01:27:34.920 --> 01:27:38.000
Here comes Dixon! He's exhausted
from just punching the man!

1286
01:27:39.800 --> 01:27:41.080
Knock this bum out, Mase!

1287
01:27:53.120 --> 01:27:56.960
<i>What is it you said to the kid?
It ain't about how hard you hit.</i>

1288
01:27:57.160 --> 01:28:01.000
<i>It's about how hard you can get hit
and keep moving forward.</i>

1289
01:28:01.320 --> 01:28:04.840
<i>How much you can take
and keep moving forward.</i>

1290
01:28:05.000 --> 01:28:06.760
<i>- Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!
- Get up.</i>

1291
01:28:06.920 --> 01:28:08.800
<i>- Let's go! Get up!
- Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1292
01:28:09.000 --> 01:28:11.600
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1293
01:28:11.840 --> 01:28:13.640
<i>Get up.</i>

1294
01:28:33.840 --> 01:28:37.280
Another monster body shot. Rocky's
ancestors must have felt that one.

1295
01:28:37.480 --> 01:28:39.440
Come on, Rocky!
Start moving those hands!

1296
01:28:39.680 --> 01:28:41.280
Less than two minutes to go.

1297
01:28:41.480 --> 01:28:43.720
The crowd is astonished
that Balboa got up.

1298
01:28:43.880 --> 01:28:46.280
- Come on!
- Turn it over! All the way through!

1299
01:28:46.720 --> 01:28:48.320
And retaliates with fury!

1300
01:28:51.720 --> 01:28:52.880
Chop him down!

1301
01:28:56.400 --> 01:28:58.000
Come on, Rocky! Come on!

1302
01:29:00.360 --> 01:29:01.840
Take him out now!

1303
01:29:02.920 --> 01:29:04.920
They're trading shots again!

1304
01:29:05.080 --> 01:29:08.520
Balboa is trying to hit
anything and anywhere!

1305
01:29:10.760 --> 01:29:12.040
Win it! Win it!

1306
01:29:20.840 --> 01:29:21.400
Yes!

1307
01:29:21.400 --> 01:29:22.280
Yes!

1308
01:29:30.680 --> 01:29:33.400
You're a great champion.
You got heart.

1309
01:29:33.560 --> 01:29:35.240
Thanks for the opportunity.
Good man.

1310
01:29:38.160 --> 01:29:41.120
That was unbelievable. That was
the greatest thing I've ever seen.

1311
01:29:43.200 --> 01:29:45.800
You did it. That's the kind
of fighting you're talking about.

1312
01:29:47.320 --> 01:29:49.200
Hey, Paulie.

1313
01:29:49.400 --> 01:29:52.120
That beast is gone now.
The beast is out.

1314
01:29:52.280 --> 01:29:55.920
One of the most overused words
in sports, guys, is "incredible."

1315
01:29:56.080 --> 01:30:00.200
I hate to say it. This is incredible.

1316
01:30:01.520 --> 01:30:03.120
Let's go!

1317
01:30:05.760 --> 01:30:09.280
Ladies and gentlemen,
before we go to the scorecards...

1318
01:30:09.440 --> 01:30:15.280
...a round of applause for these
two heavyweight warriors!

1319
01:30:19.720 --> 01:30:23.560
We have a split decision.

1320
01:30:26.120 --> 01:30:30.760
Adelaide Byrd scores it 95-94...

1321
01:30:30.920 --> 01:30:32.680
...Dixon.

1322
01:30:33.920 --> 01:30:38.120
Chuck Giampa has it 95-94...

1323
01:30:38.280 --> 01:30:40.200
...Balboa.

1324
01:30:47.080 --> 01:30:51.720
And Bill Graham scores it 95-94...

1325
01:30:51.880 --> 01:30:56.840
...for the winner by split decision,
and still undefeated...

1326
01:30:57.000 --> 01:30:59.760
...the heavyweight champion
of the world...

1327
01:30:59.920 --> 01:31:05.400
...Mason "The Line" Dixon!

1328
01:31:07.720 --> 01:31:10.560
<i>Rocky! Rocky! Rocky!</i>

1329
01:32:00.120 --> 01:32:02.960
You know, I couldn't have
done nothing without you.

1330
01:32:05.320 --> 01:32:07.800
Yo, Adrian, we did it.

1331
01:32:14.280 --> 01:32:16.000
We did it.

